WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Alhamdulillah, O Lord of the worlds

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:07.000
The Most Gracious, the Most Merciful

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:10.000
Owner of the Day of Recompense

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:14.000
It is You we worship, and it is You we ask for help

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:17.000
Guide us to the straight path

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:21.000
The path of those upon whom You have bestowed Your Grace

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:24.000
Those who are not pleased with them, and those who are not pleased with them

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:34.940
Assalamu alaikum wa rahmatullahi wa barakatuhu

00:00:34.940 --> 00:00:36.940
In the name of Allah, the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful

00:00:36.940 --> 00:00:38.940
All praise is due to Allah, the Lord of the worlds

00:00:38.940 --> 00:00:41.940
By Him we ask for help, and we pray and salute the best of all creation

00:00:41.940 --> 00:00:46.940
Our Prophet Muhammad and his family and companions and those who follow him with kindness

00:00:46.940 --> 00:00:48.940
Until the Day of Recompense and after

00:00:48.940 --> 00:00:50.940
We praise Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:00:50.940 --> 00:00:53.940
We send blessings and salutations upon Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:00:53.940 --> 00:00:55.940
And all his companions

00:00:55.940 --> 00:00:57.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless him

00:00:57.940 --> 00:00:59.940
And may he bless them all

00:00:59.940 --> 00:01:01.940
And may he bless his entire household

00:01:01.940 --> 00:01:05.940
And may he bless all those who have struggled and strived

00:01:05.940 --> 00:01:09.940
To protect the Deen, to learn it, to practice upon it

00:01:09.940 --> 00:01:12.940
To convey it to others in a way that it has come to us

00:01:12.940 --> 00:01:15.940
Wallahi my beloved brothers and sisters

00:01:15.940 --> 00:01:17.940
It is a gift of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:01:17.940 --> 00:01:20.940
To preserve the knowledge of Islam

00:01:20.940 --> 00:01:23.940
Because the difference between us and the others

00:01:23.940 --> 00:01:26.940
Is we do not accept hearsay

00:01:26.940 --> 00:01:29.940
We need that which is sound knowledge

00:01:29.940 --> 00:01:31.940
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:01:31.940 --> 00:01:35.940
To make us from amongst those who can sacrifice at least a little bit of time

00:01:35.940 --> 00:01:37.940
To learn the Deen

00:01:37.940 --> 00:01:40.940
And we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to accept it from us

00:01:40.940 --> 00:01:43.940
And to grant us every form of goodness

00:01:43.940 --> 00:01:48.940
We saw the greatest migration or Hijra in history

00:01:48.940 --> 00:01:52.940
In fact it is the only one worth making mention of

00:01:52.940 --> 00:01:57.940
And by the arrival of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:01:58.940 --> 00:02:00.940
A new chapter commenced

00:02:00.940 --> 00:02:02.940
What was the chapter?

00:02:02.940 --> 00:02:07.940
Now Revelation had become known as Al-Madani

00:02:07.940 --> 00:02:10.940
That which was revealed in Madinah Munawwara

00:02:10.940 --> 00:02:12.940
That which was revealed after the Hijra

00:02:12.940 --> 00:02:16.940
Up to that stage Revelation was known as Al-Makki

00:02:16.940 --> 00:02:18.940
If you look at the Surahs of the Quran

00:02:18.940 --> 00:02:20.940
It says Surat so and so Makkiya

00:02:20.940 --> 00:02:22.940
Surat so and so Madaniya

00:02:22.940 --> 00:02:26.940
Did you know that most of the Surahs were already revealed?

00:02:26.940 --> 00:02:28.940
In Makkah al-Mukarrama

00:02:28.940 --> 00:02:32.940
Only 23 Surahs were revealed in Madinah Munawwara

00:02:32.940 --> 00:02:34.940
Although some of them were long like Surah Baqara

00:02:34.940 --> 00:02:38.940
And Al-Imran and so on which were revealed in Madinah Munawwara

00:02:38.940 --> 00:02:40.940
They were quite long but the number of Surahs

00:02:40.940 --> 00:02:44.940
The bulk of them were already revealed in Makkah al-Mukarrama

00:02:44.940 --> 00:02:47.940
And they were discussing the topic of Tawheed

00:02:47.940 --> 00:02:54.940
Meaning the oneness of Allah protecting ourselves from associating any form of deity with Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:02:54.940 --> 00:02:56.940
Any god with Allah

00:02:56.940 --> 00:03:02.940
So that was the core subject that was discussed in the verses that were revealed in Makkah al-Mukarrama

00:03:02.940 --> 00:03:04.940
Also as we've explained before

00:03:04.940 --> 00:03:06.940
What is known as Imaniyat

00:03:06.940 --> 00:03:08.940
Belief in life after death

00:03:08.940 --> 00:03:11.940
Belief in heaven and hell

00:03:11.940 --> 00:03:13.940
Jannah and Jahannam and so on

00:03:13.940 --> 00:03:16.940
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to grant us strength

00:03:16.940 --> 00:03:18.940
And to make us from those who are solid believers

00:03:18.940 --> 00:03:23.940
And we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to make us from those who appreciate the fact

00:03:23.940 --> 00:03:27.940
That we are the members of the Ummah of Muhammad salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:03:27.940 --> 00:03:31.940
So the Hijra calendar had commenced

00:03:31.940 --> 00:03:33.940
Now one might ask a question

00:03:33.940 --> 00:03:36.940
Did they start counting from that point?

00:03:36.940 --> 00:03:37.940
The answer is no

00:03:37.940 --> 00:03:41.940
At the time of Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu later on

00:03:41.940 --> 00:03:44.940
After the time of Abu Bakr al-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:03:44.940 --> 00:03:48.940
When Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu started recording dates

00:03:48.940 --> 00:03:53.940
He decided that it should be commenced from the Hijra

00:03:53.940 --> 00:03:57.940
And this was the decision made by Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu

00:03:57.940 --> 00:04:00.940
Now we learnt yesterday that Muhammad salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:04:00.940 --> 00:04:04.940
Arrived in Quba on the 12th of Rabi' al-Awwal

00:04:04.940 --> 00:04:07.940
And it was a Monday according to some of the narrations

00:04:07.940 --> 00:04:11.940
And according to the Christian calendar

00:04:11.940 --> 00:04:16.940
It was approximately the 20th of September 622 AD

00:04:16.940 --> 00:04:20.940
Approximately the 20th of September 622 AD

00:04:20.940 --> 00:04:25.940
So the calendar had started with the first month being Muharram

00:04:25.940 --> 00:04:26.940
Why was that?

00:04:26.940 --> 00:04:30.940
Why wasn't the first month Rabi' al-Awwal or Rabi' al-Thani?

00:04:30.940 --> 00:04:34.940
The answer to that some of the scholars have made mention of a beautiful response

00:04:34.940 --> 00:04:37.940
Even Ibn Hajar al-Asqalani has spoken about it

00:04:37.940 --> 00:04:43.940
That at that time the treaty or the pledge of Aqabah

00:04:43.940 --> 00:04:48.940
The second one was signed in the month of Dhul-Hijjah

00:04:48.940 --> 00:04:52.940
And the first Hijra commenced thereafter

00:04:52.940 --> 00:04:55.940
The moon they saw after that was the moon of Muharram

00:04:55.940 --> 00:04:57.940
So they will start counting from Muharram

00:04:57.940 --> 00:05:02.940
So Muharram was when the Hijra had commenced as a whole

00:05:02.940 --> 00:05:05.940
Not necessarily just the messenger salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:05:05.940 --> 00:05:08.940
But all his companions at large they had started

00:05:08.940 --> 00:05:12.940
And by that time the moon that was sighted was the moon of Muharram

00:05:12.940 --> 00:05:15.940
So the calendar started from the first of Muharram

00:05:15.940 --> 00:05:20.940
And this is why we have the months in that particular order in our calendar

00:05:20.940 --> 00:05:22.940
Which is the Hijra calendar

00:05:22.940 --> 00:05:25.940
So this is also a point as we said of great importance

00:05:25.940 --> 00:05:29.940
The reason why I took some time to mention this is because

00:05:29.940 --> 00:05:32.940
It is relevant to us on a day to day basis

00:05:32.940 --> 00:05:33.940
And we use this calendar

00:05:33.940 --> 00:05:36.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us strength

00:05:36.940 --> 00:05:39.940
When the Prophet salallahu alaihi wa sallam got to Quba

00:05:39.940 --> 00:05:41.940
As we made mention

00:05:41.940 --> 00:05:45.940
He had stayed in the house of al-Kulthum ibn al-Hidm

00:05:45.940 --> 00:05:49.940
According to one narration that was the pronunciation of the name

00:05:49.940 --> 00:05:54.940
And this man was one of the leaders of Banu Amr ibn Awf in Quba

00:05:54.940 --> 00:05:59.940
A few days later Ali ibn Abi Talib radiallahu anhu arrived in Quba

00:05:59.940 --> 00:06:01.940
And this is where he met Rasulullah salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:06:01.940 --> 00:06:05.940
Remember he was left behind in order to give whatever

00:06:05.940 --> 00:06:09.940
Amana and trust was entrusted to Rasulullah salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:06:09.940 --> 00:06:11.940
By the Mushriks of Makkah

00:06:11.940 --> 00:06:15.940
And this is why he stayed back and he gave all those belongings

00:06:15.940 --> 00:06:17.940
To the people whom they belonged to

00:06:17.940 --> 00:06:20.940
And then he proceeded to al-Madinah al-Munawwara

00:06:20.940 --> 00:06:24.940
And he arrived in Quba where he met Rasulullah salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:06:24.940 --> 00:06:28.940
Two or three nights after the Prophet salallahu alaihi wa sallam had arrived

00:06:28.940 --> 00:06:32.940
And the Prophet salallahu alaihi wa sallam loved the Ansar

00:06:32.940 --> 00:06:36.940
The Ansar are the helpers, the people of Madinah al-Munawwara

00:06:36.940 --> 00:06:38.940
Those who opened their homes

00:06:38.940 --> 00:06:41.940
And those who loved those who came to them

00:06:41.940 --> 00:06:43.940
Today when we have a visitor in our home

00:06:43.940 --> 00:06:46.940
Sometimes depending on who exactly it is

00:06:46.940 --> 00:06:49.940
We might feel for a while that you know this person is welcome

00:06:49.940 --> 00:06:53.940
We are excited and two three days later it becomes a bit of a burden

00:06:53.940 --> 00:06:55.940
Allahu Akbar, it becomes a burden

00:06:55.940 --> 00:06:57.940
Sometimes from day one it's a burden already

00:06:57.940 --> 00:07:00.940
Especially with the hospitality of today

00:07:00.940 --> 00:07:03.940
But there Muhammad salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:07:03.940 --> 00:07:05.940
Not just him who was welcomed

00:07:05.940 --> 00:07:08.940
Every single one of the believers

00:07:08.940 --> 00:07:11.940
The common factor was you at la ilaha illallah

00:07:11.940 --> 00:07:14.940
Muhammad al-Rasulullah salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:07:14.940 --> 00:07:16.940
And so do we, you are welcome into our homes

00:07:16.940 --> 00:07:19.940
And do you know what they did? Subhanallah

00:07:19.940 --> 00:07:22.940
At some stage they opened their doors

00:07:22.940 --> 00:07:25.940
They shared their wealth, they shared their property

00:07:25.940 --> 00:07:27.940
They shared absolutely everything

00:07:27.940 --> 00:07:29.940
And they became known as brothers

00:07:29.940 --> 00:07:31.940
Obviously this was a little bit later on

00:07:31.940 --> 00:07:33.940
When the Prophet salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:07:33.940 --> 00:07:37.940
A few days after that arrived in Al-Madinah al-Munawwara from Quba

00:07:37.940 --> 00:07:40.940
Which was in the outskirts of Madinah at the time

00:07:40.940 --> 00:07:43.940
So the Prophet salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:07:43.940 --> 00:07:46.940
Loved the Ansar so much that in Sahih al-Bukhari

00:07:46.940 --> 00:07:49.940
There is a hadith which says that Rasulullah salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:07:49.940 --> 00:07:50.940
Had said

00:07:53.940 --> 00:07:54.940
If it wasn't for the Hijra

00:07:54.940 --> 00:07:56.940
I would have been a member of the Ansar

00:07:56.940 --> 00:07:59.940
Subhanallah, which means these people

00:07:59.940 --> 00:08:01.940
They opened their arms to Islam

00:08:01.940 --> 00:08:03.940
Unlike the people of Quraish

00:08:03.940 --> 00:08:06.940
Who had harmed, who had caused lots of problems and so on

00:08:06.940 --> 00:08:11.940
All this was also for a reason known to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:08:11.940 --> 00:08:14.940
The hikmah of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala is known to him

00:08:14.940 --> 00:08:16.940
Sometimes we might pick up a point or two

00:08:16.940 --> 00:08:18.940
But in most cases we wouldn't know

00:08:18.940 --> 00:08:20.940
What was the reasoning of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:08:20.940 --> 00:08:23.940
But we surrendered to it, know it or not

00:08:23.940 --> 00:08:28.940
So this was one of the narrations mentioned by Rasulullah salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:08:28.940 --> 00:08:30.940
Another point that is worth noting

00:08:30.940 --> 00:08:34.940
How many days did the Prophet salallahu alaihi wa sallam spend in Quba?

00:08:34.940 --> 00:08:38.940
There are some narrations which make mention of a minimum of four days

00:08:38.940 --> 00:08:41.940
Whereas there is a maximum of 19 days

00:08:41.940 --> 00:08:44.940
The majority of narrations say approximately two weeks

00:08:44.940 --> 00:08:46.940
So approximately two weeks

00:08:46.940 --> 00:08:50.940
What happened in Quba was the Prophet salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:08:50.940 --> 00:08:52.940
Built a masjid

00:08:52.940 --> 00:08:54.940
That would have taken a little bit of time

00:08:54.940 --> 00:08:57.940
Although it was not as we ended of yesterday

00:08:57.940 --> 00:08:59.940
If you remember the question I asked right at the end

00:08:59.940 --> 00:09:03.940
About the beautification of the houses of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:09:03.940 --> 00:09:08.940
At that time the hearts of those who went to the house of Allah were beautified

00:09:08.940 --> 00:09:11.940
But the houses of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala were simple

00:09:11.940 --> 00:09:15.940
Nowadays the houses of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala are beautified

00:09:15.940 --> 00:09:18.940
Are our hearts as beautiful?

00:09:18.940 --> 00:09:20.940
That's the question I ended with yesterday

00:09:20.940 --> 00:09:22.940
And subhanallah it is a potent question

00:09:22.940 --> 00:09:26.940
Because it is the beautification of the heart

00:09:26.940 --> 00:09:29.940
That is achieved through the closeness of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:09:29.940 --> 00:09:32.940
And Rasulullah salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:09:32.940 --> 00:09:35.940
That will result in the solution to all our problems and difficulties

00:09:35.940 --> 00:09:39.940
And it will drive us closer to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:09:39.940 --> 00:09:43.940
So let us really spend some time with our own hearts

00:09:43.940 --> 00:09:45.940
The condition of my heart

00:09:45.940 --> 00:09:48.940
Today the difficulty is everyone is worried about the other man

00:09:48.940 --> 00:09:49.940
He is like this, he is like that

00:09:49.940 --> 00:09:52.940
In the process we forget about what we are

00:09:52.940 --> 00:09:55.940
And what amount of soup we are in

00:09:55.940 --> 00:09:59.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us and grant us goodness

00:09:59.940 --> 00:10:03.940
So Rasulullah salallahu alaihi wa sallam built this Masjid

00:10:03.940 --> 00:10:05.940
Known as Masjid Quba

00:10:05.940 --> 00:10:08.940
And Allah has praised this Masjid in the Quran

00:10:08.940 --> 00:10:09.940
And Allah calls it

00:10:13.940 --> 00:10:16.940
That Masjid which was built upon piety

00:10:16.940 --> 00:10:18.940
The reason for it to be built

00:10:18.940 --> 00:10:22.940
Those who helped in it and why it was built was piety

00:10:22.940 --> 00:10:24.940
To bring people closer to Allah

00:10:24.940 --> 00:10:26.940
To be a place where they could meet

00:10:26.940 --> 00:10:28.940
Where they could discuss their issues

00:10:28.940 --> 00:10:29.940
Where they could learn

00:10:29.940 --> 00:10:32.940
Where they could disseminate the knowledge they had

00:10:32.940 --> 00:10:36.940
Where they could prepare for any attack of the enemy

00:10:36.940 --> 00:10:38.940
Where they could prepare to retaliate

00:10:38.940 --> 00:10:41.940
And at the same time where they could pray their Salah

00:10:41.940 --> 00:10:42.940
Where they could meet the messenger

00:10:42.940 --> 00:10:44.940
Where they could learn more of the Quran

00:10:44.940 --> 00:10:47.940
And the sayings of Muhammad salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:10:47.940 --> 00:10:49.940
This was the role of the Masjid

00:10:49.940 --> 00:10:51.940
And this is why Masjid Quba was built

00:10:51.940 --> 00:10:53.940
And it became a base automatically

00:10:53.940 --> 00:10:55.940
And thereafter the Prophet salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:10:55.940 --> 00:10:57.940
Sent a message to Madina Munawwara to the Ansar

00:10:57.940 --> 00:11:00.940
That I now intend to come to Al Madina

00:11:00.940 --> 00:11:04.940
And then they sent delegations to pick him up basically

00:11:04.940 --> 00:11:06.940
From amongst them some of their leaders

00:11:06.940 --> 00:11:07.940
And some of their people

00:11:07.940 --> 00:11:09.940
And a lot of them came with some weapons

00:11:09.940 --> 00:11:10.940
Because they were worried

00:11:10.940 --> 00:11:13.940
They had encircled Muhammad salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:11:13.940 --> 00:11:15.940
They did not want the enemy from Quraysh

00:11:15.940 --> 00:11:17.940
Or the enemy from amongst the tribes

00:11:17.940 --> 00:11:19.940
Who may be jealous around

00:11:19.940 --> 00:11:22.940
To harm Muhammad salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:11:22.940 --> 00:11:24.940
So for that reason they had come in and encircled him

00:11:24.940 --> 00:11:26.940
And they took him subhanallah

00:11:26.940 --> 00:11:28.940
And this was a Friday

00:11:28.940 --> 00:11:30.940
On a Friday it is reported

00:11:30.940 --> 00:11:32.940
Rasulullah salallahu alaihi wa sallam departed

00:11:32.940 --> 00:11:37.940
And he started going from Quba to Madina Munawwara

00:11:37.940 --> 00:11:41.940
And on the way as some of the narrations make mention

00:11:41.940 --> 00:11:43.940
It was the time of Jumu'ah

00:11:43.940 --> 00:11:46.940
Now As'ad ibn Zurara radiallahu anhu

00:11:46.940 --> 00:11:49.940
He before Jumu'ah was made compulsory

00:11:49.940 --> 00:11:51.940
Already used to gather the Muslims on a Friday

00:11:51.940 --> 00:11:54.940
He already used to gather the Muslims on a Friday

00:11:54.940 --> 00:11:55.940
And they used to talk

00:11:55.940 --> 00:11:57.940
They used to engage in Ibadah and so on

00:11:57.940 --> 00:11:58.940
Read their Salah

00:11:58.940 --> 00:12:01.940
And thereafter when Muhammad salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:12:01.940 --> 00:12:03.940
Was proceeding from Quba

00:12:03.940 --> 00:12:05.940
Going to Madina Munawwara

00:12:05.940 --> 00:12:08.940
The time of that Salah of Jumu'ah

00:12:08.940 --> 00:12:10.940
Came into place

00:12:10.940 --> 00:12:14.940
And he stopped at a place known as Banu Salim ibn Awf

00:12:14.940 --> 00:12:19.940
And today if you look at just outside Masjid Quba

00:12:19.940 --> 00:12:22.940
There is a little Masjid known as Masjid al-Jumu'ah

00:12:22.940 --> 00:12:25.940
Some narrations say that that is where the Jumu'ah took place

00:12:25.940 --> 00:12:28.940
One of the khutbas of Muhammad salallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:12:28.940 --> 00:12:31.940
Some narrations say that was his first khutba

00:12:31.940 --> 00:12:35.940
The first lecture ever delivered to the Ansar and the muhajireen

00:12:35.940 --> 00:12:37.940
Was at that particular point

00:12:37.940 --> 00:12:39.940
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala knows best

00:12:39.940 --> 00:12:41.940
But the wording of it is very interesting

00:12:41.940 --> 00:12:42.940
He says oh people

00:12:42.940 --> 00:12:45.940
He warns them about Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:12:45.940 --> 00:12:48.940
And about the meeting with Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:12:48.940 --> 00:12:50.940
The importance to take the leader

00:12:50.940 --> 00:12:54.940
Where he says you were like a flock without a shepherd

00:12:54.940 --> 00:12:56.940
And Allah gave you the shepherd

00:12:56.940 --> 00:12:57.940
And he is going to question you

00:12:57.940 --> 00:12:58.940
What did you do?

00:12:58.940 --> 00:13:02.940
Did you follow or did you lead yourself astray?

00:13:02.940 --> 00:13:05.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala make us followers

00:13:05.940 --> 00:13:09.940
And then he says fear, the punishment of hell

00:13:09.940 --> 00:13:14.940
Even if it means by a small piece of a date

00:13:14.940 --> 00:13:17.940
Giving a charity by a piece of a date

00:13:17.940 --> 00:13:19.940
Not even a full date, a piece of a date

00:13:19.940 --> 00:13:22.940
And if you cannot give that amount of a charity

00:13:22.940 --> 00:13:25.940
Then at least by a good word

00:13:25.940 --> 00:13:26.940
Mention good words

00:13:26.940 --> 00:13:28.940
And this shows us that your sadaqah

00:13:28.940 --> 00:13:30.940
And the charities that you give and I give

00:13:30.940 --> 00:13:35.940
They have a role to play in saving myself and yourselves from hell fire

00:13:35.940 --> 00:13:37.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us

00:13:37.940 --> 00:13:39.940
Many people take it for granted

00:13:39.940 --> 00:13:42.940
The one rand or one dollar, one riyal that we give

00:13:42.940 --> 00:13:45.940
In the path of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:13:45.940 --> 00:13:48.940
That perhaps could be a means of our saviour

00:13:48.940 --> 00:13:49.940
From the fire of Jahannam

00:13:49.940 --> 00:13:52.940
So do not belittle even a single donation

00:13:52.940 --> 00:13:55.940
In the right cause towards the poor and the needy

00:13:55.940 --> 00:13:57.940
And the cause of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:13:57.940 --> 00:13:59.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us sustenance

00:13:59.940 --> 00:14:01.940
And may he make us content

00:14:01.940 --> 00:14:03.940
May he make us people who are happy at all times

00:14:03.940 --> 00:14:06.940
So this was a khutba and the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:14:06.940 --> 00:14:09.940
Then proceeded and progressed to al-madinatul munawwara

00:14:09.940 --> 00:14:11.940
And there subhanallah

00:14:11.940 --> 00:14:14.940
Just try and picture the excitement

00:14:14.940 --> 00:14:15.940
The people were so happy

00:14:15.940 --> 00:14:17.940
Their messenger was coming

00:14:17.940 --> 00:14:19.940
They had accepted Islam already

00:14:19.940 --> 00:14:22.940
The bulk of them had accepted Islam already

00:14:22.940 --> 00:14:24.940
They had heard so much about this man

00:14:24.940 --> 00:14:25.940
First time meeting him

00:14:25.940 --> 00:14:27.940
Imagine you hear so much about someone

00:14:27.940 --> 00:14:29.940
And they've really taught you so much

00:14:29.940 --> 00:14:32.940
And now you're going to see them for the first time

00:14:32.940 --> 00:14:33.940
Subhanallah

00:14:33.940 --> 00:14:34.940
The excitement

00:14:34.940 --> 00:14:37.940
This was a nabi of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:14:37.940 --> 00:14:38.940
The highest of creation

00:14:38.940 --> 00:14:40.940
And he is moving subhanallah

00:14:40.940 --> 00:14:42.940
The creatures of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:14:42.940 --> 00:14:44.940
Are at peace with him

00:14:44.940 --> 00:14:46.940
Starting from the clouds to the trees

00:14:46.940 --> 00:14:47.940
To the stones to the animals

00:14:47.940 --> 00:14:49.940
Everything at peace with him

00:14:49.940 --> 00:14:52.940
And he is moving with this delegation of people

00:14:52.940 --> 00:14:54.940
And at that particular time subhanallah

00:14:54.940 --> 00:14:56.940
People used to climb on their roofs

00:14:56.940 --> 00:14:58.940
In order to look at what was going on

00:14:58.940 --> 00:15:00.940
So you find the women climbing up on their roofs

00:15:00.940 --> 00:15:02.940
And the men had rushed out

00:15:02.940 --> 00:15:04.940
The children had rushed out

00:15:04.940 --> 00:15:07.940
And there is a narration in sahih muslim

00:15:07.940 --> 00:15:09.940
Which makes mention of the young boys

00:15:09.940 --> 00:15:11.940
And the youngsters of madina munawwara

00:15:11.940 --> 00:15:14.940
Chanting a few words

00:15:14.940 --> 00:15:16.940
The chanting of the words

00:15:16.940 --> 00:15:18.940
Ya muhammad ya rasoolallah

00:15:18.940 --> 00:15:20.940
Ya rasoolallah ya muhammad

00:15:20.940 --> 00:15:22.940
These words and many other words

00:15:22.940 --> 00:15:24.940
Are made mention of in the books of hadith

00:15:24.940 --> 00:15:26.940
And as for the books of history

00:15:26.940 --> 00:15:28.940
And I explained yesterday the difference

00:15:28.940 --> 00:15:30.940
Between the books of history and the books of hadith

00:15:30.940 --> 00:15:33.940
The books of history make mention of a song

00:15:33.940 --> 00:15:34.940
That we would all have heard

00:15:34.940 --> 00:15:37.940
Being sung by some of the young boys and girls

00:15:37.940 --> 00:15:38.940
Of madina munawwara

00:15:38.940 --> 00:15:39.940
As

00:15:44.940 --> 00:15:45.940
And so on

00:15:45.940 --> 00:15:46.940
The beautiful words

00:15:46.940 --> 00:15:48.940
These are made mention of not in the books of hadith

00:15:48.940 --> 00:15:50.940
But in the books of seerah

00:15:50.940 --> 00:15:52.940
In the books of history

00:15:52.940 --> 00:15:54.940
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to bless us

00:15:54.940 --> 00:15:58.940
Indeed it was the donning of a new time in the history

00:15:58.940 --> 00:16:00.940
Not only of madina munawwara

00:16:00.940 --> 00:16:02.940
But of the muslims at large

00:16:02.940 --> 00:16:03.940
Subhanallah

00:16:03.940 --> 00:16:04.940
And they were so happy

00:16:04.940 --> 00:16:06.940
Everyone wanting to get a glimpse

00:16:06.940 --> 00:16:07.940
It is reported subhanallah

00:16:07.940 --> 00:16:09.940
That even from amongst the jewish tribes

00:16:09.940 --> 00:16:11.940
There were three jewish tribes

00:16:11.940 --> 00:16:12.940
Banu Qaynuqa'

00:16:12.940 --> 00:16:13.940
Banu An-Nadir

00:16:13.940 --> 00:16:14.940
And Banu Qurayza

00:16:14.940 --> 00:16:16.940
They were around madina munawwara

00:16:16.940 --> 00:16:19.940
They had come from the roman empire

00:16:19.940 --> 00:16:20.940
And from the Byzantine empire

00:16:20.940 --> 00:16:22.940
They had come down south

00:16:22.940 --> 00:16:24.940
And they were also informed

00:16:24.940 --> 00:16:27.940
That a messenger would come in an area

00:16:27.940 --> 00:16:29.940
Described exactly as madina munawwara

00:16:29.940 --> 00:16:31.940
And this is why they camped around there

00:16:31.940 --> 00:16:32.940
They stayed there

00:16:32.940 --> 00:16:35.940
They came and they heard his words

00:16:35.940 --> 00:16:37.940
Some of them tested him by asking him questions

00:16:37.940 --> 00:16:40.940
And many of their leaders accepted Islam

00:16:40.940 --> 00:16:41.940
Many of the people

00:16:41.940 --> 00:16:43.940
When they heard from amongst the jewish people

00:16:43.940 --> 00:16:44.940
Many of them

00:16:44.940 --> 00:16:46.940
When they heard they accepted Islam

00:16:46.940 --> 00:16:49.940
But obviously the bulk of the

00:16:49.940 --> 00:16:50.940
Ammah

00:16:50.940 --> 00:16:52.940
The bulk of the public of the jews

00:16:52.940 --> 00:16:53.940
They were waiting

00:16:53.940 --> 00:16:55.940
They were very very skeptical

00:16:55.940 --> 00:16:58.940
They did not want to give him to an arab

00:16:58.940 --> 00:16:59.940
And they said

00:16:59.940 --> 00:17:01.940
These are the children of Ismail

00:17:01.940 --> 00:17:03.940
We are the children of his haq

00:17:03.940 --> 00:17:06.940
Again it went back to the ignorance

00:17:06.940 --> 00:17:08.940
And arrogance of the people of Quraish

00:17:08.940 --> 00:17:10.940
They did not want to accept

00:17:10.940 --> 00:17:12.940
Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:17:12.940 --> 00:17:13.940
Because Abu Jahl says

00:17:13.940 --> 00:17:15.940
That you see the family of this Abu Talib

00:17:15.940 --> 00:17:18.940
They have had virtue of this and that

00:17:18.940 --> 00:17:19.940
And that and the Zamzam

00:17:19.940 --> 00:17:20.940
And now prophethood

00:17:20.940 --> 00:17:21.940
We are not going to take it

00:17:21.940 --> 00:17:22.940
We don't want it

00:17:22.940 --> 00:17:25.940
We cannot give leadership to his child

00:17:25.940 --> 00:17:26.940
Or his family

00:17:26.940 --> 00:17:27.940
Subhanallah

00:17:27.940 --> 00:17:30.940
And this is what made them deny

00:17:30.940 --> 00:17:32.940
And this is the exact point

00:17:32.940 --> 00:17:34.940
That made the jewish people deny

00:17:34.940 --> 00:17:35.940
Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:17:35.940 --> 00:17:37.940
Yet they were waiting for him

00:17:37.940 --> 00:17:39.940
And they had settled in Medina Munawwara

00:17:39.940 --> 00:17:40.940
Because of that

00:17:40.940 --> 00:17:41.940
Subhanallah

00:17:41.940 --> 00:17:43.940
And as I told you

00:17:43.940 --> 00:17:44.940
Some of their leaders

00:17:44.940 --> 00:17:45.940
In fact a lot of their leaders

00:17:45.940 --> 00:17:48.940
Had accepted Islam

00:17:48.940 --> 00:17:49.940
And from amongst them was

00:17:49.940 --> 00:17:51.940
Abdullah ibn Salam radiallahu anhu

00:17:51.940 --> 00:17:52.940
We made mention of his story

00:17:52.940 --> 00:17:54.940
And I think we should repeat it

00:17:54.940 --> 00:17:55.940
He was from amongst those

00:17:55.940 --> 00:17:57.940
He says when I saw the messenger

00:17:57.940 --> 00:17:58.940
As he came into Medina Munawwara

00:17:58.940 --> 00:18:00.940
I was busy with doing something

00:18:00.940 --> 00:18:01.940
In my little garden

00:18:01.940 --> 00:18:02.940
I left everything and I ran

00:18:02.940 --> 00:18:04.940
I saw his face

00:18:04.940 --> 00:18:06.940
Obviously he got a glimpse of it

00:18:06.940 --> 00:18:08.940
And he says as soon as I saw him

00:18:08.940 --> 00:18:10.940
I knew this is not the face of a liar

00:18:10.940 --> 00:18:11.940
Subhanallah

00:18:11.940 --> 00:18:12.940
And he says

00:18:12.940 --> 00:18:14.940
Then I heard some of his words

00:18:14.940 --> 00:18:16.940
And from amongst the first words

00:18:16.940 --> 00:18:19.940
That were uttered by Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:18:19.940 --> 00:18:21.940
Which were heard by Abdullah ibn Salam

00:18:21.940 --> 00:18:22.940
Something

00:18:22.940 --> 00:18:23.940
Subhanallah

00:18:23.940 --> 00:18:25.940
Subhanallah

00:18:25.940 --> 00:18:26.940
O people

00:18:26.940 --> 00:18:27.940
Spread peace

00:18:27.940 --> 00:18:28.940
And feed the food

00:18:28.940 --> 00:18:30.940
And reach the merciful

00:18:30.940 --> 00:18:31.940
And pray the night

00:18:31.940 --> 00:18:32.940
And the people sleep

00:18:32.940 --> 00:18:35.940
You will enter the Paradise of your Lord with peace

00:18:35.940 --> 00:18:36.940
If you notice the rhyming of it

00:18:36.940 --> 00:18:37.940
Obviously this is one of the

00:18:37.940 --> 00:18:39.940
Narrations of the Hadith

00:18:39.940 --> 00:18:40.940
There are other wordings

00:18:40.940 --> 00:18:42.940
But quite similar in meaning

00:18:42.940 --> 00:18:43.940
O people

00:18:43.940 --> 00:18:45.940
Spread the peace and the peace

00:18:45.940 --> 00:18:46.940
Live peacefully

00:18:46.940 --> 00:18:48.940
The peace has a very deep meaning

00:18:48.940 --> 00:18:49.940
It doesn't just mean

00:18:49.940 --> 00:18:51.940
Peace be upon you

00:18:51.940 --> 00:18:52.940
As in just a greeting

00:18:52.940 --> 00:18:53.940
Empty of any thought

00:18:53.940 --> 00:18:54.940
But it actually means

00:18:54.940 --> 00:18:56.940
Peace be upon you

00:18:56.940 --> 00:18:58.940
From any harm from me

00:18:58.940 --> 00:18:59.940
I won't harm you

00:18:59.940 --> 00:19:01.940
So peace be upon you

00:19:01.940 --> 00:19:02.940
So when we say

00:19:02.940 --> 00:19:03.940
Assalamu alaykum

00:19:03.940 --> 00:19:04.940
We mean

00:19:04.940 --> 00:19:05.940
I'm not going to harm you

00:19:05.940 --> 00:19:06.940
Peace be upon you

00:19:06.940 --> 00:19:07.940
Not only from me

00:19:07.940 --> 00:19:08.940
But from all the creatures

00:19:08.940 --> 00:19:09.940
Of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:19:09.940 --> 00:19:12.940
May you be at total peace

00:19:12.940 --> 00:19:13.940
Imagine a dua

00:19:13.940 --> 00:19:14.940
We are praying

00:19:14.940 --> 00:19:15.940
Whenever we meet one another

00:19:15.940 --> 00:19:16.940
For one another

00:19:16.940 --> 00:19:18.940
What greater greeting can there be

00:19:18.940 --> 00:19:19.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:19:19.940 --> 00:19:21.940
Make us from amongst those

00:19:21.940 --> 00:19:23.940
Who don't just shorten

00:19:23.940 --> 00:19:25.940
Such a powerful prayer

00:19:25.940 --> 00:19:27.940
And who can actually say it properly

00:19:27.940 --> 00:19:28.940
When we utter it

00:19:28.940 --> 00:19:29.940
And may Allah accept it from us

00:19:29.940 --> 00:19:32.940
So spread this salam

00:19:32.940 --> 00:19:34.940
And feed the people

00:19:34.940 --> 00:19:35.940
Feed not only the poor

00:19:35.940 --> 00:19:36.940
But feed others

00:19:36.940 --> 00:19:37.940
And you will find

00:19:37.940 --> 00:19:38.940
That the hearts come closer

00:19:38.940 --> 00:19:40.940
You know when you feed people

00:19:40.940 --> 00:19:41.940
Subhanallah

00:19:41.940 --> 00:19:42.940
A lot of the times

00:19:42.940 --> 00:19:43.940
What happens

00:19:43.940 --> 00:19:44.940
It is a social event

00:19:44.940 --> 00:19:45.940
That brings people together

00:19:45.940 --> 00:19:46.940
It makes you discuss things

00:19:46.940 --> 00:19:47.940
It brings you closer

00:19:47.940 --> 00:19:48.940
And so on

00:19:48.940 --> 00:19:50.940
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:19:50.940 --> 00:19:51.940
To grant us hospitality

00:19:51.940 --> 00:19:53.940
To make us hospitable people

00:19:53.940 --> 00:19:55.940
And to make us appreciative

00:19:55.940 --> 00:19:56.940
Of those who are hospitable

00:19:56.940 --> 00:19:57.940
Towards us

00:19:57.940 --> 00:19:58.940
Alhamdulillah

00:19:58.940 --> 00:20:00.940
So he says

00:20:00.940 --> 00:20:01.940
At'imu al-ta'am

00:20:01.940 --> 00:20:02.940
Feed even the poor

00:20:02.940 --> 00:20:03.940
Obviously

00:20:03.940 --> 00:20:04.940
How many of us

00:20:04.940 --> 00:20:05.940
Would be ready to invite

00:20:05.940 --> 00:20:07.940
A wealthy man

00:20:07.940 --> 00:20:08.940
Or a popular man

00:20:08.940 --> 00:20:09.940
To our homes

00:20:09.940 --> 00:20:10.940
What about the poor person

00:20:10.940 --> 00:20:11.940
Who is on your street

00:20:11.940 --> 00:20:12.940
Have you ever thought

00:20:12.940 --> 00:20:13.940
Of giving him food

00:20:13.940 --> 00:20:14.940
Subhanallah

00:20:14.940 --> 00:20:15.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:20:15.940 --> 00:20:16.940
Open our doors

00:20:16.940 --> 00:20:17.940
Wasilul arhaama

00:20:17.940 --> 00:20:19.940
And fulfill your relations

00:20:19.940 --> 00:20:20.940
Fulfill the link

00:20:20.940 --> 00:20:21.940
And the tie

00:20:21.940 --> 00:20:22.940
And the rights

00:20:22.940 --> 00:20:23.940
Of your family members

00:20:23.940 --> 00:20:25.940
And pray at night

00:20:25.940 --> 00:20:27.940
When everyone is asleep

00:20:27.940 --> 00:20:29.940
Because that is the most sincere

00:20:29.940 --> 00:20:30.940
When we pray

00:20:30.940 --> 00:20:31.940
In everybody's midst

00:20:31.940 --> 00:20:32.940
Yes there is sincerity

00:20:32.940 --> 00:20:33.940
But perhaps

00:20:33.940 --> 00:20:34.940
We are worried about

00:20:34.940 --> 00:20:35.940
This man watching

00:20:35.940 --> 00:20:36.940
That man watching

00:20:36.940 --> 00:20:37.940
So the sincerity levels

00:20:37.940 --> 00:20:38.940
Might not be that high

00:20:38.940 --> 00:20:39.940
But when you are praying

00:20:39.940 --> 00:20:40.940
At night

00:20:40.940 --> 00:20:41.940
When nobody is watching you

00:20:41.940 --> 00:20:42.940
It's between you and Allah

00:20:42.940 --> 00:20:43.940
Subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:20:43.940 --> 00:20:44.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:20:44.940 --> 00:20:45.940
Open our doors

00:20:45.940 --> 00:20:46.940
May he grant us sincerity

00:20:46.940 --> 00:20:47.940
In our deeds

00:20:47.940 --> 00:20:48.940
Then the hadith

00:20:48.940 --> 00:20:49.940
Ended by saying

00:20:49.940 --> 00:20:50.940
If you do that

00:20:50.940 --> 00:20:51.940
You will enter

00:20:51.940 --> 00:20:52.940
The paradise of your Rabb

00:20:52.940 --> 00:20:53.940
With great ease

00:20:53.940 --> 00:20:54.940
You will enter

00:20:54.940 --> 00:20:55.940
Paradise with great ease

00:20:55.940 --> 00:20:56.940
Abdullah ibn Salam

00:20:56.940 --> 00:20:57.940
Says he came

00:20:57.940 --> 00:20:58.940
And he declared

00:20:58.940 --> 00:20:59.940
His acceptance

00:20:59.940 --> 00:21:00.940
Of the Shahadah

00:21:00.940 --> 00:21:01.940
He declared that

00:21:01.940 --> 00:21:02.940
This man is indeed

00:21:02.940 --> 00:21:03.940
A messenger

00:21:03.940 --> 00:21:04.940
Sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:21:04.940 --> 00:21:05.940
And you know the story

00:21:05.940 --> 00:21:06.940
I made mention of

00:21:06.940 --> 00:21:07.940
Where the Prophet

00:21:07.940 --> 00:21:08.940
Sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:21:08.940 --> 00:21:09.940
When he found

00:21:09.940 --> 00:21:10.940
That this man was

00:21:10.940 --> 00:21:11.940
One of the leaders

00:21:11.940 --> 00:21:12.940
Of the Jewish tribes

00:21:12.940 --> 00:21:13.940
He told him

00:21:13.940 --> 00:21:14.940
That this man

00:21:14.940 --> 00:21:15.940
Was one of the leaders

00:21:15.940 --> 00:21:16.940
Of the Jewish tribes

00:21:16.940 --> 00:21:17.940
He told him

00:21:17.940 --> 00:21:18.940
What about your people

00:21:18.940 --> 00:21:19.940
He said my people

00:21:19.940 --> 00:21:20.940
Will not accept

00:21:20.940 --> 00:21:21.940
They said no

00:21:21.940 --> 00:21:22.940
Let us call them

00:21:22.940 --> 00:21:23.940
So the Rasulullah

00:21:23.940 --> 00:21:24.940
Sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:21:24.940 --> 00:21:25.940
Told him to go

00:21:25.940 --> 00:21:26.940
Behind the wall

00:21:26.940 --> 00:21:27.940
Called the people

00:21:27.940 --> 00:21:28.940
And asked him

00:21:28.940 --> 00:21:29.940
Who is this man

00:21:29.940 --> 00:21:30.940
In your midst

00:21:30.940 --> 00:21:31.940
They said

00:21:31.940 --> 00:21:32.940
He is a leader

00:21:32.940 --> 00:21:33.940
A son of a leader

00:21:33.940 --> 00:21:34.940
An honest man

00:21:34.940 --> 00:21:35.940
Son of an honest man

00:21:35.940 --> 00:21:36.940
Righteous person

00:21:36.940 --> 00:21:37.940
Son of a righteous

00:21:37.940 --> 00:21:38.940
He is this and that

00:21:38.940 --> 00:21:39.940
And they praised him

00:21:39.940 --> 00:21:40.940
So then they were told

00:21:40.940 --> 00:21:41.940
What if he has accepted Islam

00:21:41.940 --> 00:21:42.940
And they said

00:21:42.940 --> 00:21:43.940
It is impossible

00:21:43.940 --> 00:21:44.940
He won't do that

00:21:44.940 --> 00:21:45.940
So then when

00:21:45.940 --> 00:21:46.940
The Rasulullah

00:21:46.940 --> 00:21:47.940
Sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:21:47.940 --> 00:21:48.940
Called him from

00:21:48.940 --> 00:21:49.940
Behind the wall

00:21:49.940 --> 00:21:50.940
And asked him

00:21:50.940 --> 00:21:51.940
Or in fact

00:21:51.940 --> 00:21:52.940
He came out

00:21:52.940 --> 00:21:53.940
And declared his Shahada

00:21:53.940 --> 00:21:54.940
That I bear witness

00:21:54.940 --> 00:21:55.940
That Allah is one

00:21:55.940 --> 00:21:56.940
And you are indeed

00:21:56.940 --> 00:21:57.940
The final messenger

00:21:57.940 --> 00:21:58.940
Of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:21:58.940 --> 00:22:00.940
They changed their tune instantly

00:22:00.940 --> 00:22:01.940
And they said

00:22:01.940 --> 00:22:02.940
He is a liar

00:22:02.940 --> 00:22:03.940
Son of a liar

00:22:03.940 --> 00:22:04.940
He was a traitor

00:22:04.940 --> 00:22:05.940
Son of a traitor

00:22:05.940 --> 00:22:06.940
He is a cheat

00:22:06.940 --> 00:22:07.940
Son of a cheat

00:22:07.940 --> 00:22:08.940
And so on

00:22:08.940 --> 00:22:09.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:22:09.940 --> 00:22:11.940
Not make us from those

00:22:11.940 --> 00:22:13.940
Whom when clear cut signs

00:22:13.940 --> 00:22:14.940
Come in front of us

00:22:14.940 --> 00:22:15.940
We still don't surrender

00:22:15.940 --> 00:22:16.940
Allahu Akbar

00:22:16.940 --> 00:22:18.940
May Allah open our doors

00:22:18.940 --> 00:22:20.940
So this was the beauty

00:22:20.940 --> 00:22:21.940
As Nabi Sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:22:21.940 --> 00:22:23.940
Arrived in Al Madinatul Munawwara

00:22:23.940 --> 00:22:24.940
And subhanallah

00:22:24.940 --> 00:22:25.940
A beautiful day

00:22:25.940 --> 00:22:27.940
But everyone wanted

00:22:27.940 --> 00:22:29.940
Muhammad Sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:22:29.940 --> 00:22:31.940
To come to his place

00:22:31.940 --> 00:22:32.940
Obviously

00:22:32.940 --> 00:22:34.940
How did the rest of the

00:22:34.940 --> 00:22:35.940
Muhajireen

00:22:35.940 --> 00:22:36.940
Enter the homes of the Ansar

00:22:36.940 --> 00:22:38.940
How did the rest of the people

00:22:38.940 --> 00:22:39.940
Who made Hijra

00:22:39.940 --> 00:22:40.940
Enter the homes of the people

00:22:40.940 --> 00:22:42.940
Of Madinah Munawwara

00:22:42.940 --> 00:22:43.940
Very simple

00:22:43.940 --> 00:22:45.940
By what is known as qur'a

00:22:45.940 --> 00:22:46.940
Picking lots

00:22:46.940 --> 00:22:47.940
Which means

00:22:47.940 --> 00:22:49.940
They would pick the name

00:22:49.940 --> 00:22:50.940
Of the person

00:22:50.940 --> 00:22:52.940
And that particular name

00:22:52.940 --> 00:22:53.940
Would go to the next Ansari

00:22:53.940 --> 00:22:54.940
Who is waiting in line

00:22:54.940 --> 00:22:56.940
So they pick the name

00:22:56.940 --> 00:22:58.940
Nobody favored anyone

00:22:58.940 --> 00:22:59.940
And nobody chose

00:22:59.940 --> 00:23:00.940
I will go with him

00:23:00.940 --> 00:23:01.940
He will come with me

00:23:01.940 --> 00:23:02.940
No, it was picked out

00:23:02.940 --> 00:23:03.940
And subhanallah

00:23:03.940 --> 00:23:05.940
More like lots were drawn

00:23:05.940 --> 00:23:06.940
For that

00:23:06.940 --> 00:23:07.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:23:07.940 --> 00:23:08.940
Grant us exception

00:23:08.940 --> 00:23:09.940
Meaning

00:23:09.940 --> 00:23:10.940
May He accept us

00:23:10.940 --> 00:23:12.940
Today if we want to solve

00:23:12.940 --> 00:23:13.940
A problem

00:23:13.940 --> 00:23:15.940
It is also a Sunnah way

00:23:15.940 --> 00:23:16.940
To actually put all your names

00:23:16.940 --> 00:23:17.940
In the hat

00:23:17.940 --> 00:23:18.940
And pick out one

00:23:18.940 --> 00:23:19.940
There's no harm in that

00:23:19.940 --> 00:23:20.940
Because it would resolve

00:23:20.940 --> 00:23:21.940
Your matter

00:23:21.940 --> 00:23:22.940
And it means

00:23:22.940 --> 00:23:24.940
Nobody took anyone's chance

00:23:24.940 --> 00:23:26.940
Meaning anyone's side

00:23:26.940 --> 00:23:28.940
I'm just thinking of something

00:23:28.940 --> 00:23:29.940
And that made me

00:23:29.940 --> 00:23:30.940
Make a slip of the tongue

00:23:30.940 --> 00:23:31.940
That sometimes if people

00:23:31.940 --> 00:23:32.940
Want to cheat

00:23:32.940 --> 00:23:33.940
They write their name

00:23:33.940 --> 00:23:34.940
20 times

00:23:34.940 --> 00:23:35.940
So everybody thinks

00:23:35.940 --> 00:23:36.940
That there's 20 names

00:23:36.940 --> 00:23:37.940
And they're not realizing

00:23:37.940 --> 00:23:38.940
There's only one name

00:23:38.940 --> 00:23:39.940
20 times

00:23:39.940 --> 00:23:40.940
When you pick it out

00:23:40.940 --> 00:23:41.940
Anyone picks it out

00:23:41.940 --> 00:23:42.940
And the name comes

00:23:42.940 --> 00:23:43.940
That's the type of cheating

00:23:43.940 --> 00:23:44.940
People in our time

00:23:44.940 --> 00:23:45.940
Would engage in

00:23:45.940 --> 00:23:46.940
But at that time

00:23:46.940 --> 00:23:47.940
Subhanallah

00:23:47.940 --> 00:23:48.940
It was just

00:23:48.940 --> 00:23:49.940
Now with Muhammad

00:23:49.940 --> 00:23:50.940
Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:23:50.940 --> 00:23:51.940
Where would he go?

00:23:51.940 --> 00:23:52.940
So the narrations

00:23:52.940 --> 00:23:53.940
There are two narrations

00:23:53.940 --> 00:23:54.940
One makes mention of

00:23:54.940 --> 00:23:55.940
The fact that

00:23:55.940 --> 00:23:56.940
He had stopped

00:23:56.940 --> 00:23:57.940
Where his camel had stopped

00:23:57.940 --> 00:23:58.940
And he asked

00:23:58.940 --> 00:23:59.940
Whose home is the closest

00:23:59.940 --> 00:24:00.940
And Abu Ayub Al-Ansari

00:24:00.940 --> 00:24:01.940
Radhiallahu anhu

00:24:01.940 --> 00:24:02.940
Says

00:24:02.940 --> 00:24:03.940
Here's my home

00:24:03.940 --> 00:24:04.940
And here's its door

00:24:04.940 --> 00:24:05.940
So he said

00:24:05.940 --> 00:24:06.940
This is where I will stop

00:24:06.940 --> 00:24:07.940
The other narration

00:24:07.940 --> 00:24:08.940
Which is very close

00:24:09.940 --> 00:24:10.940
He was off his camel

00:24:10.940 --> 00:24:11.940
And as they said

00:24:11.940 --> 00:24:12.940
Ya Rasulallah

00:24:12.940 --> 00:24:13.940
Come to my home

00:24:13.940 --> 00:24:14.940
Come to my home

00:24:14.940 --> 00:24:15.940
And so on

00:24:15.940 --> 00:24:16.940
He said

00:24:16.940 --> 00:24:17.940
Let my camel go

00:24:17.940 --> 00:24:18.940
It has been instructed

00:24:18.940 --> 00:24:19.940
And it will stop

00:24:19.940 --> 00:24:20.940
Wherever I should be

00:24:20.940 --> 00:24:21.940
So the camel

00:24:21.940 --> 00:24:22.940
Went a little bit

00:24:22.940 --> 00:24:23.940
And paused

00:24:23.940 --> 00:24:24.940
And sat down

00:24:24.940 --> 00:24:25.940
At a specific place

00:24:25.940 --> 00:24:26.940
And the closest door

00:24:26.940 --> 00:24:27.940
Was the door

00:24:27.940 --> 00:24:28.940
Of Abu Ayub Al-Ansari

00:24:28.940 --> 00:24:29.940
Radhiallahu anhu

00:24:29.940 --> 00:24:30.940
So this is how

00:24:30.940 --> 00:24:31.940
The decision was made

00:24:31.940 --> 00:24:32.940
And the Prophet

00:24:32.940 --> 00:24:33.940
Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:24:33.940 --> 00:24:34.940
Wasallahu alaihi wasallam

00:24:34.940 --> 00:24:35.940
Wasallahu alaihi wasallam

00:24:35.940 --> 00:24:36.940
Wasallahu alaihi wasallam

00:24:36.940 --> 00:24:37.940
Wasallahu alaihi wasallam

00:24:37.940 --> 00:24:38.940
The Prophet

00:24:38.940 --> 00:24:39.940
Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:24:39.940 --> 00:24:40.940
Then went into the house

00:24:40.940 --> 00:24:42.940
Of Abu Ayub Al-Ansari

00:24:42.940 --> 00:24:43.940
He had a house

00:24:43.940 --> 00:24:44.940
Which had two floors

00:24:44.940 --> 00:24:45.940
Meaning

00:24:45.940 --> 00:24:46.940
It was a double story home

00:24:46.940 --> 00:24:47.940
And at that time

00:24:47.940 --> 00:24:50.940
The second floor

00:24:50.940 --> 00:24:51.940
There was no concrete

00:24:51.940 --> 00:24:52.940
Between the two floors

00:24:52.940 --> 00:24:53.940
So Rasulallah

00:24:53.940 --> 00:24:54.940
Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:24:54.940 --> 00:24:56.940
Had entered the base

00:24:56.940 --> 00:24:57.940
Meaning the bottom floor

00:24:57.940 --> 00:24:58.940
And Abu Ayub Al-Ansari

00:24:58.940 --> 00:25:00.940
Came with his family

00:25:00.940 --> 00:25:01.940
And he says

00:25:01.940 --> 00:25:02.940
Oh messenger

00:25:02.940 --> 00:25:04.940
Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:25:04.940 --> 00:25:05.940
I cannot allow you

00:25:05.940 --> 00:25:06.940
To be here

00:25:06.940 --> 00:25:08.940
On this ground floor

00:25:08.940 --> 00:25:10.940
When I am going to be above you

00:25:10.940 --> 00:25:11.940
I am going to be above you

00:25:11.940 --> 00:25:13.940
I can't allow that to happen

00:25:13.940 --> 00:25:15.940
You need to go above us

00:25:15.940 --> 00:25:16.940
Because as it is

00:25:16.940 --> 00:25:17.940
You are higher

00:25:17.940 --> 00:25:19.940
It is a sign of respect

00:25:19.940 --> 00:25:21.940
We would like to be below

00:25:21.940 --> 00:25:22.940
You be above

00:25:22.940 --> 00:25:24.940
Rasulallah Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:25:24.940 --> 00:25:25.940
Told him no

00:25:25.940 --> 00:25:26.940
I would prefer to be below

00:25:26.940 --> 00:25:28.940
Because people would come to meet me

00:25:28.940 --> 00:25:29.940
And it would be better

00:25:29.940 --> 00:25:31.940
For the family members

00:25:31.940 --> 00:25:33.940
Instead of people coming past

00:25:33.940 --> 00:25:34.940
The women and everyone

00:25:34.940 --> 00:25:36.940
As they come up to see me

00:25:36.940 --> 00:25:38.940
Rather I be at the bottom

00:25:38.940 --> 00:25:40.940
And you can be at the top

00:25:40.940 --> 00:25:41.940
Without any interference

00:25:41.940 --> 00:25:42.940
And it is reported

00:25:42.940 --> 00:25:46.940
That they were so well behaved

00:25:46.940 --> 00:25:48.940
Meaning the children and the family

00:25:48.940 --> 00:25:50.940
They were all so well behaved

00:25:50.940 --> 00:25:52.940
That they did not want to walk

00:25:52.940 --> 00:25:54.940
In a way that would disturb

00:25:54.940 --> 00:25:55.940
Rasulallah Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:25:55.940 --> 00:25:56.940
Not only that

00:25:56.940 --> 00:25:58.940
It is reported that

00:25:58.940 --> 00:26:00.940
One of the urns

00:26:00.940 --> 00:26:01.940
That were holding water

00:26:01.940 --> 00:26:03.940
Happened to fall and break

00:26:03.940 --> 00:26:05.940
There on the top floor

00:26:05.940 --> 00:26:07.940
And immediately they got up

00:26:07.940 --> 00:26:09.940
And they tried to wipe it out so fast

00:26:09.940 --> 00:26:10.940
Because they didn't want the water

00:26:10.940 --> 00:26:11.940
To trickle down

00:26:11.940 --> 00:26:14.940
And to harm Rasulallah Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:26:14.940 --> 00:26:15.940
So this narration is also

00:26:15.940 --> 00:26:17.940
Made mention of in the books of hadith

00:26:17.940 --> 00:26:20.940
As well as in the books of history and seerah

00:26:20.940 --> 00:26:21.940
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:26:21.940 --> 00:26:23.940
To make us from amongst those

00:26:23.940 --> 00:26:25.940
Who can respect the level

00:26:25.940 --> 00:26:27.940
Of Rasulallah Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:26:27.940 --> 00:26:28.940
And at the same time

00:26:28.940 --> 00:26:30.940
Respect the level of the ulama

00:26:30.940 --> 00:26:32.940
Because

00:26:32.940 --> 00:26:34.940
The ulama are those who have

00:26:34.940 --> 00:26:36.940
Inherited from the anbiya

00:26:36.940 --> 00:26:37.940
They will have knowledge

00:26:37.940 --> 00:26:38.940
Sound knowledge

00:26:38.940 --> 00:26:39.940
They will teach

00:26:39.940 --> 00:26:40.940
And they will relay

00:26:40.940 --> 00:26:42.940
The message of the messengers

00:26:42.940 --> 00:26:44.940
And the treatment that people

00:26:44.940 --> 00:26:46.940
Give the scholars of Islam

00:26:46.940 --> 00:26:48.940
Will be similar to the treatment

00:26:48.940 --> 00:26:50.940
That people gave the messengers

00:26:50.940 --> 00:26:51.940
Because the message is one

00:26:51.940 --> 00:26:53.940
And this is why you find

00:26:53.940 --> 00:26:55.940
Societies break up

00:26:55.940 --> 00:26:57.940
Into exactly the same groups of people

00:26:57.940 --> 00:26:58.940
You have hypocrites

00:26:58.940 --> 00:26:59.940
You have people

00:26:59.940 --> 00:27:00.940
Who will support the ulama

00:27:00.940 --> 00:27:01.940
You have people

00:27:01.940 --> 00:27:02.940
Who will go down in history

00:27:02.940 --> 00:27:04.940
As those who crumbled communities

00:27:04.940 --> 00:27:06.940
Because they fought the ulama

00:27:06.940 --> 00:27:07.940
And so on

00:27:07.940 --> 00:27:08.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:27:08.940 --> 00:27:10.940
Let us die in a condition

00:27:10.940 --> 00:27:12.940
That we are on the right side

00:27:12.940 --> 00:27:13.940
Remember

00:27:13.940 --> 00:27:15.940
Not every time should things happen

00:27:15.940 --> 00:27:17.940
The way you want them to happen

00:27:17.940 --> 00:27:19.940
They should always happen the way

00:27:19.940 --> 00:27:21.940
Allah and His Rasul want them to happen

00:27:21.940 --> 00:27:22.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:27:22.940 --> 00:27:24.940
Grant us goodness

00:27:24.940 --> 00:27:25.940
Allahu Akbar

00:27:25.940 --> 00:27:27.940
So this was the house of Rasulallah Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:27:27.940 --> 00:27:29.940
This was the house of Abu Ayyub al-Ansari

00:27:29.940 --> 00:27:30.940
Radiyallahu anhu

00:27:30.940 --> 00:27:32.940
Beautiful place

00:27:32.940 --> 00:27:34.940
Where the Prophet Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:27:34.940 --> 00:27:35.940
Stayed

00:27:35.940 --> 00:27:37.940
And in no time

00:27:37.940 --> 00:27:39.940
Something else happened

00:27:39.940 --> 00:27:41.940
There was need for a place

00:27:41.940 --> 00:27:42.940
For the Muslims to gather

00:27:42.940 --> 00:27:44.940
Because up to that stage

00:27:44.940 --> 00:27:45.940
For a day or two

00:27:45.940 --> 00:27:47.940
They had gathered for Salah

00:27:47.940 --> 00:27:48.940
Wherever they were

00:27:48.940 --> 00:27:49.940
They had read Salah

00:27:49.940 --> 00:27:51.940
When the Salah time had come in

00:27:51.940 --> 00:27:53.940
They read it wherever they were

00:27:53.940 --> 00:27:55.940
Then the Prophet Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:27:55.940 --> 00:27:56.940
Chose a place

00:27:56.940 --> 00:27:58.940
Where the Masjid would be built

00:27:58.940 --> 00:28:00.940
And again there is a narration

00:28:00.940 --> 00:28:02.940
Of his camel being released

00:28:02.940 --> 00:28:04.940
And sitting at a specific place

00:28:04.940 --> 00:28:06.940
There is also a narration

00:28:06.940 --> 00:28:07.940
In the books of history

00:28:07.940 --> 00:28:09.940
So here we have

00:28:09.940 --> 00:28:11.940
A situation where

00:28:11.940 --> 00:28:13.940
A piece of land is located

00:28:13.940 --> 00:28:15.940
And now they are looking

00:28:15.940 --> 00:28:16.940
For the owners of this land

00:28:16.940 --> 00:28:17.940
Who happen to be

00:28:17.940 --> 00:28:19.940
Two young orphans

00:28:19.940 --> 00:28:21.940
From Banin Najjah

00:28:21.940 --> 00:28:22.940
Two orphans

00:28:22.940 --> 00:28:23.940
Little boys

00:28:23.940 --> 00:28:24.940
Meaning young men

00:28:24.940 --> 00:28:25.940
And these boys

00:28:25.940 --> 00:28:26.940
They had said

00:28:26.940 --> 00:28:28.940
Look, we can give this

00:28:28.940 --> 00:28:29.940
Just for free

00:28:29.940 --> 00:28:31.940
Meaning we can give it as a gift

00:28:31.940 --> 00:28:32.940
This land

00:28:32.940 --> 00:28:35.940
Although they didn't have anything

00:28:35.940 --> 00:28:37.940
But Rasulullah Sallallahu alaihi wasallam said

00:28:37.940 --> 00:28:39.940
No, we will pay for it

00:28:39.940 --> 00:28:40.940
And he paid for it

00:28:40.940 --> 00:28:41.940
And he gave them their price

00:28:41.940 --> 00:28:43.940
And thereafter

00:28:43.940 --> 00:28:44.940
The place was cleared

00:28:44.940 --> 00:28:45.940
Because there were trees there

00:28:45.940 --> 00:28:46.940
It was like an orchard

00:28:46.940 --> 00:28:48.940
And they had cleared the trees

00:28:48.940 --> 00:28:49.940
And so on

00:28:49.940 --> 00:28:51.940
And they had put a little bit of a

00:28:51.940 --> 00:28:52.940
Demarcation

00:28:52.940 --> 00:28:53.940
To demarcate

00:28:53.940 --> 00:28:54.940
That this is going to be

00:28:54.940 --> 00:28:57.940
The Masjid of Rasulullah Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:28:57.940 --> 00:28:59.940
Al-Masjidun Nabawi

00:28:59.940 --> 00:29:00.940
The original structure

00:29:00.940 --> 00:29:01.940
Was very small

00:29:01.940 --> 00:29:02.940
Very simple

00:29:02.940 --> 00:29:03.940
Subhanallah

00:29:03.940 --> 00:29:05.940
And it did not take them too long

00:29:05.940 --> 00:29:06.940
To get it ready

00:29:06.940 --> 00:29:07.940
For your information

00:29:07.940 --> 00:29:08.940
No carpet

00:29:08.940 --> 00:29:09.940
No marble

00:29:09.940 --> 00:29:10.940
No tiles

00:29:10.940 --> 00:29:11.940
No concrete

00:29:11.940 --> 00:29:12.940
All they did was cleared it

00:29:12.940 --> 00:29:13.940
And that's it

00:29:13.940 --> 00:29:14.940
So when they made Sajda

00:29:14.940 --> 00:29:16.940
They had marks on their knees

00:29:16.940 --> 00:29:17.940
Marks on their toes

00:29:17.940 --> 00:29:19.940
Marks on their hands

00:29:19.940 --> 00:29:20.940
And marks on their foreheads

00:29:20.940 --> 00:29:21.940
Subhanallah

00:29:21.940 --> 00:29:23.940
And what type of a roof did they have?

00:29:23.940 --> 00:29:25.940
They had a roof made up of

00:29:25.940 --> 00:29:27.940
The stumps of the palm tree

00:29:27.940 --> 00:29:29.940
And a little bit of the

00:29:29.940 --> 00:29:31.940
The branches of the palm tree

00:29:31.940 --> 00:29:33.940
That were all put together

00:29:33.940 --> 00:29:34.940
And crossed together

00:29:34.940 --> 00:29:35.940
And they had had that

00:29:35.940 --> 00:29:37.940
And that would be the roof

00:29:37.940 --> 00:29:38.940
At that particular time

00:29:38.940 --> 00:29:39.940
This is how it was

00:29:39.940 --> 00:29:41.940
How high was it?

00:29:41.940 --> 00:29:42.940
It was not very high

00:29:42.940 --> 00:29:43.940
Such that a young boy

00:29:43.940 --> 00:29:45.940
If he had to put his hand up

00:29:45.940 --> 00:29:47.940
He would be able to touch the roof

00:29:47.940 --> 00:29:48.940
He would be able to touch

00:29:48.940 --> 00:29:50.940
What we would term the ceiling

00:29:50.940 --> 00:29:51.940
So it was not very high

00:29:51.940 --> 00:29:53.940
And right next to it

00:29:53.940 --> 00:29:54.940
With it

00:29:54.940 --> 00:29:55.940
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:29:55.940 --> 00:29:58.940
Had instructed the building of two rooms

00:29:58.940 --> 00:29:59.940
For his wives

00:29:59.940 --> 00:30:02.940
Now Sawda bint Zam'a radiallahu anha

00:30:02.940 --> 00:30:04.940
She was the wife of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:30:04.940 --> 00:30:06.940
And he had married Aisha

00:30:06.940 --> 00:30:07.940
Radiallahu anha

00:30:07.940 --> 00:30:08.940
Before Hijra

00:30:08.940 --> 00:30:10.940
And now after Hijra

00:30:10.940 --> 00:30:12.940
After some time

00:30:12.940 --> 00:30:14.940
When they finally lived together

00:30:14.940 --> 00:30:16.940
That was her home

00:30:16.940 --> 00:30:18.940
Hujrat Aisha al-Siddiqa radiallahu anha

00:30:18.940 --> 00:30:20.940
And that is the home where

00:30:20.940 --> 00:30:21.940
Ultimately Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:30:21.940 --> 00:30:22.940
Passed away

00:30:22.940 --> 00:30:24.940
And that is where he is buried today

00:30:24.940 --> 00:30:25.940
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:30:25.940 --> 00:30:27.940
Grant us a lesson

00:30:27.940 --> 00:30:30.940
So these houses were built very low

00:30:30.940 --> 00:30:32.940
If you had a youngster stand up

00:30:32.940 --> 00:30:34.940
He could actually feel the top

00:30:34.940 --> 00:30:37.940
This is how the books have made mention of it

00:30:37.940 --> 00:30:40.940
And Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:30:40.940 --> 00:30:43.940
When they were building this masjid

00:30:43.940 --> 00:30:44.940
They had a habit

00:30:44.940 --> 00:30:45.940
They were so excited

00:30:45.940 --> 00:30:46.940
Because they had peace

00:30:46.940 --> 00:30:47.940
For the first time

00:30:47.940 --> 00:30:48.940
They had peace

00:30:48.940 --> 00:30:51.940
Imagine the gift of peace and security

00:30:51.940 --> 00:30:53.940
Is one of the biggest gifts you can have

00:30:53.940 --> 00:30:55.940
And you don't realize it

00:30:55.940 --> 00:30:57.940
Until you don't have it

00:30:57.940 --> 00:30:59.940
Or you only realize it

00:30:59.940 --> 00:31:00.940
If you have not had it in the past

00:31:00.940 --> 00:31:01.940
And now you have it

00:31:01.940 --> 00:31:03.940
So the Muslims were so happy

00:31:03.940 --> 00:31:05.940
They were chanting

00:31:05.940 --> 00:31:06.940
As they were working

00:31:06.940 --> 00:31:08.940
Taking the bricks and making them

00:31:08.940 --> 00:31:11.940
And any Sahabi who knew anything about building

00:31:11.940 --> 00:31:13.940
There were some who had come from afar

00:31:13.940 --> 00:31:16.940
Who were experts in mixing the sand

00:31:16.940 --> 00:31:18.940
And so on and making the clay

00:31:18.940 --> 00:31:19.940
They were called in

00:31:19.940 --> 00:31:20.940
And they were helping

00:31:20.940 --> 00:31:21.940
Subhanallah

00:31:21.940 --> 00:31:24.940
He made use of all the experts of building

00:31:24.940 --> 00:31:26.940
And at that particular time

00:31:26.940 --> 00:31:28.940
They were also chanting

00:31:28.940 --> 00:31:29.940
They had this habit of chanting

00:31:29.940 --> 00:31:32.940
A few little poems as they worked

00:31:32.940 --> 00:31:34.940
Up to today sometimes you notice

00:31:34.940 --> 00:31:35.940
People who work very hard

00:31:35.940 --> 00:31:36.940
They chant something

00:31:36.940 --> 00:31:37.940
They say a few words

00:31:37.940 --> 00:31:38.940
Just to make it light

00:31:38.940 --> 00:31:40.940
Let's hope that these words are good

00:31:40.940 --> 00:31:41.940
That time they were always good

00:31:41.940 --> 00:31:44.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:31:44.940 --> 00:31:45.940
So these words made mention of

00:31:45.940 --> 00:31:46.940
In Sahih al-Bukhari

00:31:46.940 --> 00:31:49.940
Allahumma la aisha illa aisha al-akhirah

00:31:49.940 --> 00:31:52.940
Fansulil ansara wal muhajirah

00:31:52.940 --> 00:31:53.940
O Allah there is no life

00:31:53.940 --> 00:31:55.940
Besides the life of the akhirah

00:31:55.940 --> 00:31:57.940
Ya Allah this life is nothing

00:31:57.940 --> 00:32:00.940
The life of the akhirah is what is important

00:32:00.940 --> 00:32:02.940
And the dua is

00:32:02.940 --> 00:32:04.940
So O Allah help the ansar

00:32:04.940 --> 00:32:06.940
And help the muhajireen

00:32:06.940 --> 00:32:08.940
Help those who are from Madinah

00:32:08.940 --> 00:32:09.940
Who are the helpers

00:32:09.940 --> 00:32:11.940
And help those who have migrated

00:32:11.940 --> 00:32:12.940
All the way from Mecca

00:32:12.940 --> 00:32:14.940
And come to Al-Madinah al-Munawwara

00:32:14.940 --> 00:32:15.940
This is just one of the statements

00:32:15.940 --> 00:32:17.940
That they were uttering

00:32:17.940 --> 00:32:20.940
Now, once they were building this masjid

00:32:20.940 --> 00:32:23.940
Before the masjid was completed

00:32:23.940 --> 00:32:24.940
There was the death

00:32:24.940 --> 00:32:26.940
Of one of the sahabah r.a

00:32:26.940 --> 00:32:28.940
Who was he?

00:32:28.940 --> 00:32:31.940
His name was As'ad ibn Zurara r.a

00:32:31.940 --> 00:32:33.940
He passed away

00:32:33.940 --> 00:32:35.940
Before the completion of the building

00:32:35.940 --> 00:32:37.940
Of al-masjid al-nabawi

00:32:37.940 --> 00:32:40.940
He had met Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wasallam in Madinah

00:32:40.940 --> 00:32:41.940
Remember?

00:32:41.940 --> 00:32:43.940
He was from amongst those first ones

00:32:43.940 --> 00:32:45.940
Who had pledged with Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:32:45.940 --> 00:32:47.940
Once, twice, thrice

00:32:47.940 --> 00:32:49.940
And then they came to Al-Madinah al-Munawwara

00:32:49.940 --> 00:32:50.940
And he passed away

00:32:50.940 --> 00:32:53.940
Look at what Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:32:53.940 --> 00:32:55.940
Had created him for

00:32:55.940 --> 00:32:56.940
To support the cause

00:32:56.940 --> 00:32:57.940
Subhanallah

00:32:57.940 --> 00:32:59.940
So he had passed away

00:32:59.940 --> 00:33:01.940
Another person who passed away as well

00:33:01.940 --> 00:33:03.940
Was Damurah ibn Jundub

00:33:03.940 --> 00:33:07.940
He was a person who was from Makkah al-Mukarrama

00:33:07.940 --> 00:33:11.940
He had fallen very ill

00:33:11.940 --> 00:33:13.940
Before he could make the Hijra

00:33:13.940 --> 00:33:14.940
So he told his relatives

00:33:14.940 --> 00:33:15.940
Look, take me out

00:33:15.940 --> 00:33:16.940
I want to make Hijra

00:33:16.940 --> 00:33:18.940
Because the prophet has instructed us

00:33:18.940 --> 00:33:19.940
To make Hijra

00:33:19.940 --> 00:33:21.940
Although I am very sick

00:33:21.940 --> 00:33:22.940
And he passed away

00:33:22.940 --> 00:33:25.940
In Tan'im on the outskirts of Makkah al-Mukarrama

00:33:25.940 --> 00:33:28.940
And verses were revealed

00:33:28.940 --> 00:33:31.940
In order to show the status of those

00:33:31.940 --> 00:33:34.940
Who passed away whilst on the journey

00:33:34.940 --> 00:33:36.940
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala revealed verses

00:33:36.940 --> 00:33:54.940
Arabic

00:33:54.940 --> 00:33:56.940
Whosoever has come out of their homes

00:33:56.940 --> 00:33:57.940
Intending the Hijra

00:33:57.940 --> 00:33:59.940
And then they pass away

00:33:59.940 --> 00:34:02.940
Their reward is written with Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:34:02.940 --> 00:34:04.940
They will get a full reward of it

00:34:04.940 --> 00:34:05.940
Subhanallah

00:34:05.940 --> 00:34:08.940
He was also one of those who passed away

00:34:08.940 --> 00:34:11.940
Another member who was a senior member

00:34:11.940 --> 00:34:13.940
Of the Ansar who had passed away

00:34:13.940 --> 00:34:14.940
One of the twelve whom

00:34:14.940 --> 00:34:16.940
Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam had chosen

00:34:16.940 --> 00:34:18.940
To look after the people of Medina

00:34:18.940 --> 00:34:20.940
Between the pledge and the Hijra

00:34:20.940 --> 00:34:22.940
His name was Al-Baraa ibn Ma'rur

00:34:22.940 --> 00:34:24.940
And this radiallahu anhu

00:34:24.940 --> 00:34:27.940
He passed away in the month of Safar

00:34:27.940 --> 00:34:29.940
Just before Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:34:29.940 --> 00:34:31.940
Had entered Quba

00:34:31.940 --> 00:34:32.940
This man had passed away

00:34:32.940 --> 00:34:35.940
So he did not see Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:34:35.940 --> 00:34:36.940
Post Hijra

00:34:36.940 --> 00:34:38.940
But he had already met him before the Hijra

00:34:38.940 --> 00:34:40.940
He was a sahabi

00:34:40.940 --> 00:34:42.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:34:42.940 --> 00:34:44.940
Also who passed away

00:34:44.940 --> 00:34:47.940
The man whom the prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:34:47.940 --> 00:34:49.940
Stayed at his house in Quba

00:34:49.940 --> 00:34:51.940
Al-Kulthum ibn Al-Hidm

00:34:51.940 --> 00:34:53.940
Or Kulthum ibn Al-Hidm

00:34:53.940 --> 00:34:54.940
Al-Hidm

00:34:54.940 --> 00:34:55.940
This man radiallahu anhu

00:34:55.940 --> 00:34:57.940
He passed away as well

00:34:57.940 --> 00:34:59.940
Very very soon after that

00:34:59.940 --> 00:35:00.940
When the prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:35:00.940 --> 00:35:03.940
Had come into Al-Madinah Al-Munawwarah

00:35:03.940 --> 00:35:05.940
Now there is a very interesting dua

00:35:05.940 --> 00:35:06.940
That the prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:35:06.940 --> 00:35:07.940
Made in Madinah

00:35:07.940 --> 00:35:09.940
Madinah the weather is different from Makkah

00:35:09.940 --> 00:35:10.940
Totally different

00:35:10.940 --> 00:35:12.940
The cold is severe

00:35:12.940 --> 00:35:14.940
The heat is also severe

00:35:14.940 --> 00:35:15.940
And the cold has in it

00:35:15.940 --> 00:35:17.940
Or it used to have in it

00:35:17.940 --> 00:35:19.940
A sickness and a disease

00:35:19.940 --> 00:35:20.940
Known as Humma

00:35:20.940 --> 00:35:21.940
The Humma of Madinah

00:35:21.940 --> 00:35:23.940
This Humma of Yathrib in fact

00:35:23.940 --> 00:35:24.940
It was very common

00:35:24.940 --> 00:35:27.940
And it used to kill a lot of people every year

00:35:27.940 --> 00:35:29.940
So the prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:35:29.940 --> 00:35:31.940
Was told about it

00:35:31.940 --> 00:35:33.940
These are the tough conditions of

00:35:33.940 --> 00:35:34.940
Madinah Munawwarah

00:35:34.940 --> 00:35:37.940
Do you know what the hadith says to us?

00:35:37.940 --> 00:35:39.940
Man sabara ala harriha wa bardiha

00:35:39.940 --> 00:35:40.940
Dakhala al-jannah

00:35:40.940 --> 00:35:42.940
Whoever can bear patience

00:35:42.940 --> 00:35:45.940
Upon the heat and the cold of Madinah

00:35:45.940 --> 00:35:46.940
Allah will grant them jannah

00:35:46.940 --> 00:35:48.940
So don't complain of the weather

00:35:48.940 --> 00:35:50.940
You go there, it was very hot

00:35:50.940 --> 00:35:51.940
Hang on, just say Alhamdulillah

00:35:51.940 --> 00:35:53.940
We are in the blessed place

00:35:53.940 --> 00:35:54.940
That is what's important

00:35:54.940 --> 00:35:55.940
Whether it's hot or cold

00:35:55.940 --> 00:35:56.940
Is besides the point

00:35:56.940 --> 00:35:58.940
Subhanallah

00:35:58.940 --> 00:36:00.940
You know I sit and I think of people

00:36:00.940 --> 00:36:01.940
May Allah protect us

00:36:01.940 --> 00:36:03.940
For sports, what would they do?

00:36:03.940 --> 00:36:05.940
They would buy their tickets well in advance

00:36:05.940 --> 00:36:07.940
They would go for the whole season

00:36:07.940 --> 00:36:08.940
And they would go to Europe

00:36:08.940 --> 00:36:09.940
Even in the hottest

00:36:09.940 --> 00:36:12.940
Even if their fasts happened to have been the longest

00:36:12.940 --> 00:36:13.940
But they will still go

00:36:13.940 --> 00:36:15.940
And to them, they went for a purpose

00:36:15.940 --> 00:36:17.940
To kick a ball or to watch people kicking a ball

00:36:17.940 --> 00:36:19.940
To throw a little piece

00:36:19.940 --> 00:36:21.940
And to watch people throwing a discus and so on

00:36:21.940 --> 00:36:24.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala safeguard us

00:36:24.940 --> 00:36:25.940
We have the deen

00:36:25.940 --> 00:36:27.940
When we go to the holy lands

00:36:27.940 --> 00:36:29.940
Never ever complain about the weather

00:36:29.940 --> 00:36:31.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala take us there

00:36:31.940 --> 00:36:32.940
Again and again

00:36:32.940 --> 00:36:35.940
Who knows perhaps in the heat of the moment

00:36:35.940 --> 00:36:37.940
Or the cold of Madinah

00:36:37.940 --> 00:36:39.940
That might be the moment of acceptance of your dua

00:36:39.940 --> 00:36:41.940
And you might be a person who is granted jannah

00:36:41.940 --> 00:36:42.940
Because of that dua

00:36:42.940 --> 00:36:45.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant that to us

00:36:45.940 --> 00:36:47.940
So he made a dua

00:36:47.940 --> 00:36:48.940
He says

00:36:48.940 --> 00:36:49.940
He says

00:36:53.940 --> 00:36:56.940
O Allah, make us love Madinah

00:36:56.940 --> 00:36:57.940
As much as we love Makkah

00:36:57.940 --> 00:36:58.940
Makkah is your birth place

00:36:58.940 --> 00:36:59.940
We all know the birth place

00:36:59.940 --> 00:37:01.940
You always go back there

00:37:01.940 --> 00:37:02.940
Some people marry and they travel

00:37:02.940 --> 00:37:04.940
But their hearts are still stuck somewhere

00:37:04.940 --> 00:37:05.940
Where they were born

00:37:05.940 --> 00:37:06.940
And when they go back there

00:37:06.940 --> 00:37:08.940
Everything seems to be greeting them

00:37:08.940 --> 00:37:09.940
You see why?

00:37:09.940 --> 00:37:10.940
Because you look at this familiar

00:37:10.940 --> 00:37:12.940
You look at that familiar, mashaAllah

00:37:12.940 --> 00:37:13.940
See all the smiles

00:37:13.940 --> 00:37:15.940
I see there are some jama'is that we have here as well

00:37:15.940 --> 00:37:16.940
MashaAllah

00:37:16.940 --> 00:37:17.940
Some sons-in-law

00:37:17.940 --> 00:37:18.940
Perhaps that we have here

00:37:18.940 --> 00:37:20.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors

00:37:20.940 --> 00:37:21.940
Believe me

00:37:21.940 --> 00:37:22.940
It's a happy moment

00:37:22.940 --> 00:37:24.940
To go and see your home once again

00:37:24.940 --> 00:37:26.940
So the hearts were connected

00:37:26.940 --> 00:37:29.940
To the birth place of Rasulullah

00:37:29.940 --> 00:37:31.940
Which was Makkah

00:37:31.940 --> 00:37:32.940
So now he's making a dua

00:37:32.940 --> 00:37:35.940
O Allah, grant us the love of Madinah

00:37:35.940 --> 00:37:36.940
As we love Makkah

00:37:36.940 --> 00:37:37.940
And even more

00:37:37.940 --> 00:37:38.940
Subhanallah

00:37:38.940 --> 00:37:40.940
And that love has become even more

00:37:40.940 --> 00:37:41.940
Subhanallah

00:37:41.940 --> 00:37:43.940
In terms of spirituality

00:37:43.940 --> 00:37:45.940
The salah and the place

00:37:45.940 --> 00:37:46.940
Which is most sacred

00:37:46.940 --> 00:37:47.940
Is the Haram in Makkah

00:37:47.940 --> 00:37:48.940
Without a doubt

00:37:48.940 --> 00:37:49.940
Immediately after that

00:37:49.940 --> 00:37:50.940
The Haram in Madinah

00:37:50.940 --> 00:37:51.940
Without a doubt

00:37:51.940 --> 00:37:52.940
Immediately after that

00:37:52.940 --> 00:37:53.940
The Haram in Jerusalem

00:37:53.940 --> 00:37:54.940
Without a doubt

00:37:54.940 --> 00:37:55.940
That brings me to a point

00:37:55.940 --> 00:37:57.940
When the Masjid was built

00:37:57.940 --> 00:37:59.940
Which way was the Qibla?

00:37:59.940 --> 00:38:00.940
Interesting question

00:38:00.940 --> 00:38:02.940
It was facing Jerusalem

00:38:02.940 --> 00:38:04.940
We as Muslimin initially

00:38:04.940 --> 00:38:07.940
Were instructed to face Jerusalem

00:38:07.940 --> 00:38:10.940
In order to create uniformity

00:38:10.940 --> 00:38:11.940
When we pray

00:38:11.940 --> 00:38:12.940
That was it

00:38:12.940 --> 00:38:15.940
The reason why we face a specific direction

00:38:15.940 --> 00:38:16.940
Is for uniformity

00:38:16.940 --> 00:38:18.940
We don't worship any stones

00:38:18.940 --> 00:38:20.940
Or any people and so on

00:38:20.940 --> 00:38:22.940
But it is to create uniformity

00:38:22.940 --> 00:38:24.940
No rich man must come and say

00:38:24.940 --> 00:38:26.940
Hang on, face it towards my house

00:38:26.940 --> 00:38:27.940
Or the other one says

00:38:27.940 --> 00:38:28.940
You know what?

00:38:28.940 --> 00:38:29.940
I'm going to put something here

00:38:29.940 --> 00:38:30.940
You must face it in this direction

00:38:30.940 --> 00:38:31.940
Or I don't like this building

00:38:31.940 --> 00:38:32.940
This way, put it this way

00:38:32.940 --> 00:38:34.940
No, no one has a say

00:38:34.940 --> 00:38:35.940
It's the house of Allah

00:38:35.940 --> 00:38:36.940
He decides which way it faces

00:38:36.940 --> 00:38:38.940
So he decided at that time

00:38:38.940 --> 00:38:39.940
It must face Jerusalem

00:38:39.940 --> 00:38:42.940
That was the house of Allah

00:38:42.940 --> 00:38:43.940
Subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:38:43.940 --> 00:38:47.940
That was built by Ibrahim A.S. as well

00:38:47.940 --> 00:38:48.940
In Jerusalem

00:38:48.940 --> 00:38:49.940
You find Masjid Al-Aqsa

00:38:49.940 --> 00:38:51.940
So we used to face in that direction

00:38:51.940 --> 00:38:54.940
Now, the Prophet S.A.W

00:38:54.940 --> 00:38:55.940
Made this dua

00:38:55.940 --> 00:38:57.940
The continuation of the dua

00:38:57.940 --> 00:38:58.940
He says

00:38:58.940 --> 00:39:03.940
O Allah, make it pure for us to live in

00:39:03.940 --> 00:39:05.940
This Medina Munawwara

00:39:05.940 --> 00:39:07.940
Purified, Ya Allah

00:39:07.940 --> 00:39:08.940
Subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:39:08.940 --> 00:39:09.940
From what?

00:39:09.940 --> 00:39:11.940
This disease that is in it

00:39:11.940 --> 00:39:12.940
The Prophet S.A.W

00:39:12.940 --> 00:39:14.940
The Prophet S.A.W says

00:39:17.940 --> 00:39:19.940
O Allah, take this disease

00:39:19.940 --> 00:39:22.940
That comes in it every year

00:39:22.940 --> 00:39:25.940
And place it outside Medina Munawwara

00:39:25.940 --> 00:39:27.940
In a place known as Juhfa

00:39:27.940 --> 00:39:28.940
And it's reported that from that time

00:39:28.940 --> 00:39:30.940
This sickness was gone

00:39:30.940 --> 00:39:31.940
It disappeared

00:39:31.940 --> 00:39:32.940
People did not get sick

00:39:32.940 --> 00:39:34.940
With that humma of Yathrib thereafter

00:39:34.940 --> 00:39:35.940
They didn't

00:39:35.940 --> 00:39:37.940
This was a miracle of nubuwa

00:39:37.940 --> 00:39:39.940
The miracle of Rasulullah S.A.W

00:39:39.940 --> 00:39:40.940
He made a dua

00:39:40.940 --> 00:39:41.940
And this disease

00:39:41.940 --> 00:39:42.940
This sickness

00:39:42.940 --> 00:39:43.940
This influenza or flu

00:39:43.940 --> 00:39:44.940
Whatever it was

00:39:44.940 --> 00:39:47.940
Which used to take the lives of so many people

00:39:47.940 --> 00:39:48.940
Every year

00:39:48.940 --> 00:39:49.940
It stopped

00:39:49.940 --> 00:39:50.940
And it was gone out

00:39:50.940 --> 00:39:52.940
And it went into a specific place

00:39:52.940 --> 00:39:53.940
Known as Juhfa

00:39:53.940 --> 00:39:54.940
According to the narrations

00:39:54.940 --> 00:39:56.940
In Sahih al-Bukhari

00:39:56.940 --> 00:39:59.940
And then he made another dua

00:40:02.940 --> 00:40:04.940
O Allah, grant us baraka

00:40:04.940 --> 00:40:06.940
In the sustenance that is achieved here

00:40:06.940 --> 00:40:08.940
In Medina Munawwara

00:40:08.940 --> 00:40:10.940
The wording of the dua is

00:40:10.940 --> 00:40:13.940
Grant us baraka in the measurement

00:40:13.940 --> 00:40:16.940
And in the handfuls that we give and take

00:40:16.940 --> 00:40:17.940
Sa' is a measurement

00:40:17.940 --> 00:40:18.940
It is actually a measurement

00:40:18.940 --> 00:40:19.940
Where they used to measure

00:40:19.940 --> 00:40:21.940
When they used to give and take

00:40:21.940 --> 00:40:23.940
Some of the flour and the wheat and so on

00:40:23.940 --> 00:40:24.940
And the mud

00:40:24.940 --> 00:40:26.940
When they used to give some other items

00:40:26.940 --> 00:40:28.940
They used to measure it with their hands

00:40:28.940 --> 00:40:30.940
So ya Allah, put baraka in it

00:40:30.940 --> 00:40:32.940
Wallahi, my beloved brothers and sisters

00:40:32.940 --> 00:40:34.940
I need to tell you something

00:40:34.940 --> 00:40:37.940
That you can bear witness regarding

00:40:37.940 --> 00:40:39.940
Do you see the dates?

00:40:39.940 --> 00:40:43.940
You can have dates from anywhere in the world

00:40:43.940 --> 00:40:46.940
But pick up a date from Medina Munawwara

00:40:46.940 --> 00:40:47.940
It has a different taste in it

00:40:47.940 --> 00:40:48.940
Do you bear witness?

00:40:48.940 --> 00:40:49.940
Subhanallah

00:40:49.940 --> 00:40:52.940
You can pick up a date from anywhere in the world

00:40:52.940 --> 00:40:55.940
You can tell this is a Kalahari date

00:40:55.940 --> 00:40:57.940
This is another date from elsewhere

00:40:57.940 --> 00:40:59.940
This is an Algerian date

00:40:59.940 --> 00:41:00.940
You can tell it

00:41:00.940 --> 00:41:01.940
And believe me

00:41:01.940 --> 00:41:03.940
The date of Medina Munawwara

00:41:03.940 --> 00:41:05.940
It has a totally different taste to it

00:41:05.940 --> 00:41:06.940
And a sweetness in it

00:41:06.940 --> 00:41:08.940
Perhaps it is this dua of Muhammad

00:41:08.940 --> 00:41:10.940
Sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:41:10.940 --> 00:41:12.940
That has granted it such baraka

00:41:12.940 --> 00:41:14.940
Because this was included in the dua

00:41:14.940 --> 00:41:15.940
Mentioned in Sahih al-Bukhari

00:41:15.940 --> 00:41:18.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:41:18.940 --> 00:41:22.940
The Hijra was an instruction

00:41:22.940 --> 00:41:23.940
Of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:41:23.940 --> 00:41:26.940
So everyone was instructed

00:41:26.940 --> 00:41:27.940
To fulfill the Hijra

00:41:27.940 --> 00:41:29.940
Whoever didn't, they were sinful

00:41:29.940 --> 00:41:32.940
The only people who were not sinful

00:41:32.940 --> 00:41:34.940
Were those who were unable

00:41:34.940 --> 00:41:35.940
Either because they were blocked

00:41:35.940 --> 00:41:37.940
They were stopped or they didn't have the means

00:41:37.940 --> 00:41:38.940
And so on

00:41:38.940 --> 00:41:41.940
But if people were able to fulfill the Hijra

00:41:41.940 --> 00:41:42.940
And they did not

00:41:42.940 --> 00:41:43.940
They were sinful

00:41:43.940 --> 00:41:46.940
So the Hijra was farad

00:41:46.940 --> 00:41:47.940
It was compulsory upon all

00:41:47.940 --> 00:41:50.940
The bulk of the people had actually made Hijra

00:41:50.940 --> 00:41:51.940
In fact at some stage

00:41:51.940 --> 00:41:54.940
When Rasulullah Sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:41:54.940 --> 00:41:57.940
Had settled down in Al-Madeenatul Munawwara

00:41:57.940 --> 00:41:59.940
He sent Subhanallah

00:41:59.940 --> 00:42:01.940
Zayd ibn Haritha and Abu Rafi'a to Mecca

00:42:01.940 --> 00:42:02.940
To collect the rest of his

00:42:02.940 --> 00:42:05.940
And Abu Bakr As-Siddiq radiallahu anhu's families

00:42:05.940 --> 00:42:08.940
So who came all together?

00:42:08.940 --> 00:42:10.940
Fatima, the daughter of Rasulullah Sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:42:10.940 --> 00:42:12.940
And his other daughter Um Kulthum

00:42:12.940 --> 00:42:15.940
And Sawda, the wife of Rasulullah Sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:42:15.940 --> 00:42:17.940
Ibn Tizan'a radiallahu anha

00:42:17.940 --> 00:42:21.940
Ummu Ayman, the second mother

00:42:21.940 --> 00:42:23.940
Of Rasulullah Sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:42:23.940 --> 00:42:25.940
We made mention of her

00:42:25.940 --> 00:42:27.940
At the beginning of these episodes

00:42:27.940 --> 00:42:28.940
When we spoke about the woman

00:42:28.940 --> 00:42:30.940
Who looked after Rasulullah Sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:42:31.940 --> 00:42:34.940
By this time she was married to Zayd ibn Haritha

00:42:34.940 --> 00:42:37.940
Zayd ibn Haritha was the one who went to go and collect them

00:42:37.940 --> 00:42:40.940
And I think I made mention of this incident

00:42:40.940 --> 00:42:42.940
That the Prophet Sallallahu alaihi wa sallam said

00:42:42.940 --> 00:42:44.940
Whoever wants to marry a woman from paradise

00:42:44.940 --> 00:42:46.940
Should marry Ummu Ayman

00:42:46.940 --> 00:42:49.940
And Zayd ibn Haritha married her

00:42:49.940 --> 00:42:52.940
He was as fair as anything in complexion

00:42:52.940 --> 00:42:55.940
And she was dark in complexion being from Africa

00:42:55.940 --> 00:42:57.940
And he did not even doubt

00:42:57.940 --> 00:42:59.940
The minute Muhammad Sallallahu alaihi wa sallam said

00:42:59.940 --> 00:43:02.940
Whoever wants to marry a woman from paradise

00:43:02.940 --> 00:43:04.940
Should marry Ummu Ayman, he married her

00:43:04.940 --> 00:43:07.940
And they had a blessed child Usamah ibn Zayd

00:43:07.940 --> 00:43:09.940
Who was born just before the Hijrah

00:43:09.940 --> 00:43:12.940
And he had also been brought into Madinah Munawarah

00:43:12.940 --> 00:43:14.940
Together with his mother Ummu Ayman

00:43:14.940 --> 00:43:17.940
And the Usamah ibn Zayd

00:43:17.940 --> 00:43:20.940
As for Zaynab, the daughter of Rasulullah Sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:43:20.940 --> 00:43:23.940
She was married to a man known as Abu al-Aas ibn al-Rabi'

00:43:23.940 --> 00:43:25.940
He did not accept Islam

00:43:25.940 --> 00:43:28.940
And he stopped his daughter from going through the Hijrah

00:43:28.940 --> 00:43:31.940
So she was from amongst those who was excused at that particular time

00:43:31.940 --> 00:43:34.940
Together with them, the family of Abu Bakr

00:43:34.940 --> 00:43:36.940
As-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:43:36.940 --> 00:43:38.940
Ummu Oman radiallahu anhu

00:43:38.940 --> 00:43:41.940
The wife of Abu Bakr, As-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:43:41.940 --> 00:43:43.940
Aisha radiallahu anhu

00:43:43.940 --> 00:43:45.940
The wife of Rasulullah Sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:43:45.940 --> 00:43:47.940
Asma'ah binti Abi Bakr

00:43:47.940 --> 00:43:51.940
Who was the wife of Az-Zubair ibn al-Awwam radiallahu anhu

00:43:51.940 --> 00:43:54.940
And this Asma'ah, she was pregnant

00:43:54.940 --> 00:43:57.940
And when she came into Madinah Munawarah

00:43:57.940 --> 00:44:01.940
She delivered a child whose name was Abdullah ibn al-Zubair

00:44:01.940 --> 00:44:04.940
The son of Az-Zubair ibn al-Awwam radiallahu anhu

00:44:04.940 --> 00:44:06.940
This man, remember this name

00:44:06.940 --> 00:44:08.940
Abdullah ibn al-Zubair

00:44:08.940 --> 00:44:10.940
The grandchild of Abu Bakr

00:44:10.940 --> 00:44:12.940
As-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:44:12.940 --> 00:44:14.940
And the son of Az-Zubair ibn al-Awwam

00:44:14.940 --> 00:44:16.940
The son of Asma'ah binti Abi Bakr

00:44:16.940 --> 00:44:20.940
He was the first to be born from amongst the Muhajireen

00:44:20.940 --> 00:44:22.940
After the Hijrah, amazing

00:44:22.940 --> 00:44:25.940
So this was the first child of the Muhajireen

00:44:25.940 --> 00:44:27.940
Born in Madinah Munawarah

00:44:27.940 --> 00:44:30.940
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us blessing

00:44:30.940 --> 00:44:33.940
Wallahi, it is the city of Rasul

00:44:33.940 --> 00:44:35.940
Sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:44:35.940 --> 00:44:38.940
And indeed it is a very very blessed city

00:44:38.940 --> 00:44:41.940
We can feel it from the outskirts as we are drawing near

00:44:41.940 --> 00:44:43.940
The calmness, the serenity

00:44:43.940 --> 00:44:45.940
This is just the gift of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:44:45.940 --> 00:44:49.940
So these were the people who had come through

00:44:49.940 --> 00:44:52.940
And Abdullah, the son of Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:44:52.940 --> 00:44:54.940
Had also come through

00:44:55.940 --> 00:44:58.940
What had happened is the masjid was now built

00:44:58.940 --> 00:44:59.940
The people were settling in

00:44:59.940 --> 00:45:03.940
There were a few conditions around in Madinah Munawarah

00:45:03.940 --> 00:45:05.940
Perhaps we will divulge

00:45:05.940 --> 00:45:07.940
Meaning we will expand on it tomorrow

00:45:07.940 --> 00:45:09.940
By the will of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:45:09.940 --> 00:45:13.940
But today we want to make mention of the history of Adhan

00:45:13.940 --> 00:45:17.940
Because Adhan is the call which is called to the prayer

00:45:17.940 --> 00:45:19.940
They used to get together for the time of prayer

00:45:19.940 --> 00:45:23.940
And they sat to discuss with Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wa sallam

00:45:23.940 --> 00:45:24.940
What should we do?

00:45:24.940 --> 00:45:26.940
To remind the people it's prayer time

00:45:26.940 --> 00:45:28.940
So some people suggested

00:45:28.940 --> 00:45:30.940
Let us raise a flag when it's prayer time

00:45:30.940 --> 00:45:33.940
And then they said no we don't want to do that

00:45:33.940 --> 00:45:34.940
For whatever reason

00:45:34.940 --> 00:45:37.940
And perhaps this flag it's not one of our ways of doing things

00:45:37.940 --> 00:45:41.290
Then some of them suggested

00:45:41.290 --> 00:45:42.290
Okay let's light a fire

00:45:42.290 --> 00:45:44.290
So the smoke will go around

00:45:44.290 --> 00:45:46.290
And we will be able to

00:45:46.290 --> 00:45:49.290
Let the people know that this is now the time of Salah

00:45:49.290 --> 00:45:50.290
They disagreed with that as well

00:45:50.290 --> 00:45:51.290
We don't light fires

00:45:51.290 --> 00:45:52.290
Then they said

00:45:52.290 --> 00:45:54.290
Okay let us blow in a bugle

00:45:54.290 --> 00:45:56.290
They said no we won't blow a bugle

00:45:56.290 --> 00:45:59.290
Because that is the way of the non-believers

00:45:59.290 --> 00:46:00.290
Then they said

00:46:00.290 --> 00:46:03.290
Okay why don't we hit on a bell

00:46:03.290 --> 00:46:05.290
Or we ring a bell?

00:46:05.290 --> 00:46:06.290
Subhanallah

00:46:06.290 --> 00:46:07.290
Then they said no

00:46:07.290 --> 00:46:09.290
That is the Christian way of calling towards prayer

00:46:09.290 --> 00:46:10.290
So we won't do that

00:46:10.290 --> 00:46:12.290
And one of them had suggested that

00:46:12.290 --> 00:46:14.290
Why don't we call the people?

00:46:14.290 --> 00:46:15.290
We just called them

00:46:15.290 --> 00:46:18.290
So Abdullah ibn Zayd al-Ansari

00:46:18.290 --> 00:46:22.290
Was one of those who used to call the people for Salah

00:46:22.290 --> 00:46:24.290
But with no specific wording

00:46:24.290 --> 00:46:26.290
He just used to go out at the time of Salah

00:46:26.290 --> 00:46:27.290
And remind the people

00:46:27.290 --> 00:46:29.290
Come for Salah, come for Salah and so on

00:46:29.290 --> 00:46:30.290
Salah, Salah

00:46:30.290 --> 00:46:32.290
And they would call the people through

00:46:32.290 --> 00:46:35.290
And later on this was known as Tathweeb

00:46:35.290 --> 00:46:37.290
Tathweeb was after the Adhan when we go out

00:46:37.290 --> 00:46:38.290
And we tell people

00:46:38.290 --> 00:46:39.290
Come, come let's go for Salah, Salah

00:46:39.290 --> 00:46:42.290
That is a Sunnah of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:46:42.290 --> 00:46:45.290
However this man Abdullah ibn Zayd al-Ansari

00:46:45.290 --> 00:46:47.290
Radhiallahu anhu

00:46:47.290 --> 00:46:48.290
He saw a dream

00:46:48.290 --> 00:46:50.290
Just within a few days

00:46:50.290 --> 00:46:51.290
He saw a dream

00:46:51.290 --> 00:46:52.290
And in the dream

00:46:52.290 --> 00:46:54.290
A man came to him and told him

00:46:54.290 --> 00:46:56.290
Why don't you utter these words?

00:46:56.290 --> 00:46:57.290
And taught him the Adhan

00:46:57.290 --> 00:46:59.290
Exactly as we know it today

00:46:59.290 --> 00:47:00.290
Allah is the greatest

00:47:00.290 --> 00:47:02.290
I bear witness that there is none worthy of worship

00:47:02.290 --> 00:47:03.290
But Allah

00:47:03.290 --> 00:47:05.290
I bear witness that Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:47:05.290 --> 00:47:06.290
Is his messenger

00:47:06.290 --> 00:47:07.290
His worshipper

00:47:07.290 --> 00:47:09.290
Come for Salah

00:47:09.290 --> 00:47:10.290
Come for success

00:47:10.290 --> 00:47:12.290
Allah is definitely the greatest

00:47:12.290 --> 00:47:14.290
There is none worthy of worship besides Allah

00:47:14.290 --> 00:47:15.290
These are the words

00:47:15.290 --> 00:47:17.290
Of the call to prayer

00:47:17.290 --> 00:47:18.290
So when he got up

00:47:18.290 --> 00:47:20.290
He went to the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:47:20.290 --> 00:47:22.290
And he told him the dream

00:47:22.290 --> 00:47:24.290
And the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam tells him

00:47:24.290 --> 00:47:26.290
Inna ha la ru'ya haqq

00:47:26.290 --> 00:47:28.290
Indeed it is a true dream

00:47:28.290 --> 00:47:30.290
I've already been given revelation

00:47:30.290 --> 00:47:33.290
With these exact words

00:47:33.290 --> 00:47:37.290
Now comes the important part

00:47:37.290 --> 00:47:38.290
Very important point

00:47:38.290 --> 00:47:39.290
We need to learn

00:47:39.290 --> 00:47:42.290
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam looks at him and says

00:47:42.290 --> 00:47:44.290
Lakin dhalika bilal

00:47:44.290 --> 00:47:46.290
Fa inna hu anna sawtam mink

00:47:46.290 --> 00:47:49.290
Go and teach these words to Bilal

00:47:50.290 --> 00:47:56.290
Because he has a much more beautiful and louder voice than yours

00:47:56.290 --> 00:47:57.290
Amazing

00:47:57.290 --> 00:47:59.290
What do we learn from this?

00:47:59.290 --> 00:48:01.290
We learn that the Muadhin

00:48:01.290 --> 00:48:04.290
Means to be a person who has a beautiful voice

00:48:04.290 --> 00:48:06.290
Who calls the Adhan in a way

00:48:06.290 --> 00:48:10.290
That automatically attracts people towards the Salah

00:48:10.290 --> 00:48:13.290
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam grant that to us

00:48:13.290 --> 00:48:15.290
And may he make us from those

00:48:15.290 --> 00:48:17.290
Whom when we call the Adhan

00:48:17.290 --> 00:48:18.290
Everybody comes

00:48:18.290 --> 00:48:19.290
Amazing

00:48:19.290 --> 00:48:20.290
You see when you have an Adhan

00:48:20.290 --> 00:48:21.290
And it's powerful

00:48:21.290 --> 00:48:22.290
And it's called

00:48:22.290 --> 00:48:23.290
Well, people listen to it

00:48:23.290 --> 00:48:26.290
The non-believers listen to a beautiful Adhan

00:48:26.290 --> 00:48:27.290
They wait for the next one

00:48:27.290 --> 00:48:29.290
I have had people who know me

00:48:29.290 --> 00:48:30.290
Who told me

00:48:30.290 --> 00:48:32.290
That you know this particular Masjid

00:48:32.290 --> 00:48:35.290
We actually wait and listen to this call

00:48:35.290 --> 00:48:36.290
It's so sweet

00:48:36.290 --> 00:48:37.290
We don't even know what it means

00:48:37.290 --> 00:48:39.290
But we get so much sweetness

00:48:39.290 --> 00:48:42.290
Out of listening to the beauty of it

00:48:42.290 --> 00:48:43.290
And we know the tune

00:48:43.290 --> 00:48:44.290
Because obviously

00:48:44.290 --> 00:48:46.290
You know the Muadhins are known for their tunes

00:48:46.290 --> 00:48:48.290
They stick normally to one particular tune

00:48:48.290 --> 00:48:49.290
Each person

00:48:49.290 --> 00:48:51.290
And that would actually sound

00:48:51.290 --> 00:48:52.290
Not only in this world

00:48:52.290 --> 00:48:53.290
But even in the Akhirah

00:48:53.290 --> 00:48:54.290
Subhanallah

00:48:54.290 --> 00:48:55.290
The Hadith says

00:48:55.290 --> 00:48:57.290
Those who will have the tallest

00:48:57.290 --> 00:48:59.290
Or the longest necks

00:48:59.290 --> 00:49:01.290
They will be the most conspicuous

00:49:01.290 --> 00:49:02.290
On the day of judgment

00:49:02.290 --> 00:49:03.290
Will be Al Muadhinoon

00:49:03.290 --> 00:49:06.290
Those who used to call out Adhan

00:49:06.290 --> 00:49:08.290
They will be known from a distance

00:49:08.290 --> 00:49:10.290
Why? Conspicuous, very high

00:49:10.290 --> 00:49:12.290
Why will they be so high?

00:49:12.290 --> 00:49:13.290
The Hadith says

00:49:13.290 --> 00:49:15.290
If the people had known the value

00:49:15.290 --> 00:49:17.290
Of calling out the Adhan

00:49:17.290 --> 00:49:20.290
And the value of standing in the first Saf

00:49:20.290 --> 00:49:22.290
Then if they couldn't do it

00:49:22.290 --> 00:49:24.290
They would actually draw lots

00:49:24.290 --> 00:49:25.290
In order to pick up

00:49:25.290 --> 00:49:27.290
Who is the one who's going to be there?

00:49:27.290 --> 00:49:29.290
That's how serious it is

00:49:29.290 --> 00:49:31.290
And that's how well virtue

00:49:31.290 --> 00:49:34.290
Or that's how highly virtuous it is

00:49:34.290 --> 00:49:35.290
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:49:35.290 --> 00:49:36.290
Grant it to us

00:49:36.290 --> 00:49:40.290
Did you know the value of calling out the Adhan?

00:49:40.290 --> 00:49:41.290
Subhanallah

00:49:41.290 --> 00:49:42.290
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:49:42.290 --> 00:49:43.290
Grant it to us

00:49:43.290 --> 00:49:45.290
Did you know that the Muadhin

00:49:45.290 --> 00:49:47.290
Gets the full reward of everyone

00:49:47.290 --> 00:49:48.290
Who came to the Masjid

00:49:48.290 --> 00:49:49.290
All their Salahs

00:49:49.290 --> 00:49:51.290
So if we are 700 people here

00:49:51.290 --> 00:49:52.290
For example

00:49:52.290 --> 00:49:55.290
The Muadhin gets 701 Salahs

00:49:55.290 --> 00:49:56.290
Rewards for that one Salah

00:49:56.290 --> 00:49:57.290
Why?

00:49:57.290 --> 00:49:58.290
He called them to the prayer

00:49:58.290 --> 00:50:00.290
Subhanallah

00:50:00.290 --> 00:50:02.290
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:50:02.290 --> 00:50:03.290
Open our doors

00:50:03.290 --> 00:50:05.290
And sometimes we find ourselves

00:50:05.290 --> 00:50:07.290
Treading all over these people

00:50:07.290 --> 00:50:09.290
And we don't even realize their value

00:50:09.290 --> 00:50:10.290
Subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:50:10.290 --> 00:50:11.290
Grant us paradise

00:50:11.290 --> 00:50:13.290
And may He grant them paradise too

00:50:13.290 --> 00:50:16.290
So Bilal ibn Rabah radiallahu anhu

00:50:16.290 --> 00:50:17.290
Was told

00:50:17.290 --> 00:50:18.290
And subhanallah

00:50:18.290 --> 00:50:20.290
He started calling the prayer

00:50:20.290 --> 00:50:23.290
Allahu Akbar, Allahu Akbar

00:50:23.290 --> 00:50:24.290
Subhanallah

00:50:24.290 --> 00:50:26.290
Beautiful call to prayer

00:50:26.290 --> 00:50:28.290
And we know it to this day

00:50:28.290 --> 00:50:30.290
Bilal ibn Rabah was the one

00:50:30.290 --> 00:50:32.290
Who started uttering these words

00:50:32.290 --> 00:50:33.290
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:50:33.290 --> 00:50:35.290
Had two main Muadhins

00:50:35.290 --> 00:50:36.290
One was Bilal

00:50:36.290 --> 00:50:37.290
And the other one

00:50:37.290 --> 00:50:39.290
Do you remember we made mention of him?

00:50:39.290 --> 00:50:41.290
Abdullah ibn Umm Maktum

00:50:41.290 --> 00:50:42.290
The blind man

00:50:42.290 --> 00:50:43.290
Subhanallah

00:50:43.290 --> 00:50:44.290
Radiallahu anhu

00:50:44.290 --> 00:50:45.290
Jami'an

00:50:45.290 --> 00:50:46.290
May Allah be pleased with them

00:50:46.290 --> 00:50:47.290
All of them

00:50:47.290 --> 00:50:48.290
It's important for us

00:50:48.290 --> 00:50:49.290
To know these names

00:50:49.290 --> 00:50:50.290
We are going to meet these people

00:50:50.290 --> 00:50:51.290
It's important for us

00:50:51.290 --> 00:50:52.290
To know these names

00:50:52.290 --> 00:50:53.290
And to be able to recognize

00:50:53.290 --> 00:50:54.290
These people

00:50:54.290 --> 00:50:55.290
By the will of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:50:55.290 --> 00:50:57.290
So Bilal ibn Rabah

00:50:57.290 --> 00:50:58.290
In the Fajr prayer

00:50:58.290 --> 00:50:59.290
He added something

00:50:59.290 --> 00:51:01.290
What did he add?

00:51:01.290 --> 00:51:05.290
As-salaatu khayrun minannaun

00:51:05.290 --> 00:51:06.290
Subhanallah

00:51:06.290 --> 00:51:09.290
Salah is better than sleep

00:51:09.290 --> 00:51:11.290
Prayer is better than sleep

00:51:11.290 --> 00:51:12.290
He added that

00:51:12.290 --> 00:51:13.290
So the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:51:13.290 --> 00:51:14.290
Aqarrahu ala dhaalik

00:51:14.290 --> 00:51:15.290
He said

00:51:15.290 --> 00:51:16.290
Yes, that is correct

00:51:16.290 --> 00:51:17.290
You can say

00:51:17.290 --> 00:51:18.290
So up to today

00:51:18.290 --> 00:51:19.290
For the Fajr prayer

00:51:19.290 --> 00:51:20.290
We add that

00:51:20.290 --> 00:51:21.290
Subhanallah

00:51:21.290 --> 00:51:23.290
Now it's important for us to know

00:51:23.290 --> 00:51:25.290
That the Jumu'ah prayer

00:51:25.290 --> 00:51:26.290
Had one Adhan

00:51:26.290 --> 00:51:28.290
Later on at the time of

00:51:28.290 --> 00:51:29.290
Uthman ibn Affan

00:51:29.290 --> 00:51:30.290
Radiallahu anhu

00:51:30.290 --> 00:51:33.290
He introduced another second Adhan

00:51:33.290 --> 00:51:35.290
Which was also from above

00:51:35.290 --> 00:51:36.290
They used to call it

00:51:36.290 --> 00:51:37.290
From the top

00:51:37.290 --> 00:51:38.290
A high place

00:51:38.290 --> 00:51:39.290
At that time

00:51:39.290 --> 00:51:40.290
There were no minarets

00:51:40.290 --> 00:51:41.290
As we have them today

00:51:41.290 --> 00:51:42.290
No where the loud hail

00:51:42.290 --> 00:51:44.290
Is as we have them today

00:51:44.290 --> 00:51:45.290
But they used to call it

00:51:45.290 --> 00:51:46.290
From the top

00:51:46.290 --> 00:51:47.290
Above

00:51:47.290 --> 00:51:48.290
And they used to call it

00:51:48.290 --> 00:51:49.290
In a way that

00:51:49.290 --> 00:51:50.290
Everyone could hear

00:51:50.290 --> 00:51:51.290
So Uthman ibn Affan

00:51:51.290 --> 00:51:52.290
Radiallahu anhu

00:51:52.290 --> 00:51:53.290
Decided that

00:51:53.290 --> 00:51:54.290
Look, we want to

00:51:54.290 --> 00:51:55.290
Call the people

00:51:55.290 --> 00:51:56.290
So let us call them

00:51:56.290 --> 00:51:57.290
Through for Jumu'ah

00:51:57.290 --> 00:51:59.290
Another Adhan

00:51:59.290 --> 00:52:00.290
So he introduced

00:52:00.290 --> 00:52:01.290
A second Adhan

00:52:01.290 --> 00:52:02.290
Outside

00:52:02.290 --> 00:52:04.290
And Hisham ibn Abdul Malik

00:52:04.290 --> 00:52:05.290
Who was on

00:52:05.290 --> 00:52:06.290
In the Amawi Empire

00:52:06.290 --> 00:52:08.290
He is the one who told

00:52:08.290 --> 00:52:09.290
That Muadhin come inside

00:52:09.290 --> 00:52:10.290
And stand in front of

00:52:10.290 --> 00:52:12.290
The Imam

00:52:12.290 --> 00:52:14.290
So the Adhan that we have

00:52:14.290 --> 00:52:16.290
In front of the Imam

00:52:16.290 --> 00:52:18.290
That happens on a Friday

00:52:18.290 --> 00:52:19.290
Is actually

00:52:19.290 --> 00:52:20.290
The original Adhan

00:52:20.290 --> 00:52:21.290
For Jumu'ah

00:52:21.290 --> 00:52:22.290
But it was brought

00:52:22.290 --> 00:52:24.290
Into the Masjid by

00:52:24.290 --> 00:52:25.290
Hisham ibn Abdul Malik

00:52:25.290 --> 00:52:26.290
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:52:26.290 --> 00:52:27.290
Grant us goodness

00:52:27.290 --> 00:52:28.290
And may He make us

00:52:28.290 --> 00:52:29.290
From those who know

00:52:29.290 --> 00:52:31.290
The history of the Adhan

00:52:31.290 --> 00:52:33.290
Also in Ramadan

00:52:33.290 --> 00:52:34.290
Many generations

00:52:34.290 --> 00:52:35.290
Make mention of the Prophet

00:52:35.290 --> 00:52:36.290
Sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:52:36.290 --> 00:52:37.290
Having had two Adhans

00:52:37.290 --> 00:52:38.290
For Fajr

00:52:38.290 --> 00:52:39.290
One would wake up

00:52:39.290 --> 00:52:41.290
The lazy for Suhoor

00:52:41.290 --> 00:52:42.290
And the other one

00:52:42.290 --> 00:52:43.290
Would actually

00:52:43.290 --> 00:52:45.290
Get the people in for

00:52:45.290 --> 00:52:47.290
For Salatul Fajr

00:52:47.290 --> 00:52:48.290
And this is why

00:52:48.290 --> 00:52:49.290
To this day

00:52:49.290 --> 00:52:50.290
You find in a lot of

00:52:50.290 --> 00:52:51.290
The Middle Eastern countries

00:52:51.290 --> 00:52:52.290
In Ramadan

00:52:52.290 --> 00:52:53.290
They have an early Adhan

00:52:53.290 --> 00:52:54.290
Which is actually

00:52:54.290 --> 00:52:55.290
Getting you up

00:52:55.290 --> 00:52:56.290
For Tahajjud

00:52:56.290 --> 00:52:57.290
And at the same time

00:52:57.290 --> 00:52:58.290
Telling you it is now

00:52:58.290 --> 00:52:59.290
Time for Suhoor

00:52:59.290 --> 00:53:00.290
And then you have

00:53:00.290 --> 00:53:01.290
Another Adhan

00:53:01.290 --> 00:53:02.290
That is for Salatul Fajr

00:53:02.290 --> 00:53:03.290
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:53:03.290 --> 00:53:04.290
Open our doors

00:53:04.290 --> 00:53:05.290
Insha'Allah tomorrow

00:53:05.290 --> 00:53:06.290
We will go through

00:53:06.290 --> 00:53:07.290
More of what happened

00:53:07.290 --> 00:53:08.290
In the initial stages

00:53:08.290 --> 00:53:09.290
In Al-Madinah Al-Munawwara

00:53:09.290 --> 00:53:10.290
Before we go into

00:53:10.290 --> 00:53:11.290
The difficulties

00:53:11.290 --> 00:53:12.290
That were faced

00:53:12.290 --> 00:53:13.290
Once again

00:53:13.290 --> 00:53:14.290
At the hands of Quraish

00:53:14.290 --> 00:53:15.290
And the enemies of Islam

00:53:15.290 --> 00:53:16.290
Until then we say

00:53:16.290 --> 00:53:17.290
Wa sallallahu wa sallam

00:53:17.290 --> 00:53:18.290
Wa baraka ala Nabina Muhammad

00:53:18.290 --> 00:53:19.290
Subhanallahi wa bihamdih

00:53:19.290 --> 00:53:20.290
Subhanaka Allahumma

00:53:20.290 --> 00:53:21.290
Wa bihamdih

00:53:21.290 --> 00:53:22.290
Ash hadu alla ilaha illa anta

00:53:22.290 --> 00:53:23.290
Nastaghfiruka

00:53:23.290 --> 00:53:24.290
Wa natubu ilaik
